WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.876 --> 00:00:11.312
[triumphant music plays]

2
00:00:23.357 --> 00:00:25.025
[record player whirring]

3
00:00:26.561 --> 00:00:27.628
[needle scratches]

4
00:00:27.761 --> 00:00:30.197
["This Summer"
by Sleigh Bells playing]

5
00:00:37.138 --> 00:00:38.706
-[sparks fizzle]
-[dog whimpers]

6
00:01:01.695 --> 00:01:02.897
[moans sleepily]

7
00:01:03.497 --> 00:01:06.834
You managed to get most of it
on the paper this time.

8
00:01:08.269 --> 00:01:09.803
Good job. buddy.

9
00:01:11.172 --> 00:01:12.541
Okay.

10
00:01:13.107 --> 00:01:14.675
<i>Hey. hey. it's me.</i>

11
00:01:15.476 --> 00:01:16.877
<i>Happy birthday week.</i>

12
00:01:17.011 --> 00:01:18.513
<i>So. I expect</i>
<i>you're celebrating.</i>

13
00:01:18.647 --> 00:01:20.147
<i>When do you think</i>
<i>you're coming back?</i>

14
00:01:20.281 --> 00:01:21.749
<i>Let me know. 'Cause. well.</i>
<i>you know. we miss you.</i>

15
00:01:21.882 --> 00:01:22.950
<i>Okay. don't have too much--</i>

16
00:01:23.484 --> 00:01:24.553
[sighs]

17
00:01:24.685 --> 00:01:25.819
[song continues]

18
00:01:25.953 --> 00:01:27.888
[exclaims]

19
00:01:48.142 --> 00:01:49.544
[groans]

20
00:01:49.678 --> 00:01:52.279
I need a yellow sun. like. now.

21
00:02:39.628 --> 00:02:41.529
[engines roaring]

22
00:02:50.971 --> 00:02:53.374
[suspenseful music playing]

23
00:03:13.561 --> 00:03:14.529
Brigands.

24
00:03:15.963 --> 00:03:17.331
They've come for my swords.

25
00:03:17.464 --> 00:03:19.333
I guess it was only
a matter of time.

26
00:03:19.701 --> 00:03:21.201
We give them what they want...

27
00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:24.405
and then they'll leave.

28
00:03:26.373 --> 00:03:27.374
[door opens]

29
00:03:27.509 --> 00:03:30.411
[heavy footfalls]

30
00:03:48.797 --> 00:03:50.598
[chair creaks]

31
00:03:52.534 --> 00:03:53.535
[scoffs softly]

32
00:04:03.210 --> 00:04:07.081
[device buzzes]

33
00:04:08.982 --> 00:04:10.217
Mm?

34
00:04:12.853 --> 00:04:13.621
Is that pie?

35
00:04:16.791 --> 00:04:17.458
Yes.

36
00:04:18.992 --> 00:04:20.160
[grunts]

37
00:04:23.665 --> 00:04:26.066
[music playing indistinctly
on headphones]

38
00:04:38.011 --> 00:04:39.279
[gasps]

39
00:04:40.447 --> 00:04:42.449
[Brigand grunts contentedly]

40
00:04:45.018 --> 00:04:46.521
[man] I know who you are.

41
00:04:48.656 --> 00:04:50.290
Krem of the Yellow Hills.

42
00:04:50.792 --> 00:04:52.493
Then you know why I'm here.

43
00:04:52.627 --> 00:04:54.061
My life's work.

44
00:04:54.928 --> 00:04:56.196
All in the shed out back.

45
00:04:56.330 --> 00:04:57.498
Handcrafted weapons

46
00:04:57.632 --> 00:04:59.066
forged from
the strongest steel

47
00:04:59.199 --> 00:05:00.234
that you or your Brigand army

48
00:05:00.367 --> 00:05:02.302
will ever lay
your filthy eyes on.

49
00:05:02.436 --> 00:05:05.239
You have what you want.
Now leave.

50
00:05:09.544 --> 00:05:11.912
[music on headphones
continues indistinctly]

51
00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:19.486
[Krem] Show me the way.

52
00:05:20.387 --> 00:05:22.022
-[weapon clangs]
-Not you.

53
00:05:23.792 --> 00:05:25.325
Her.

54
00:05:27.227 --> 00:05:28.530
-[gasps]
-[shouts]

55
00:05:29.531 --> 00:05:30.799
[weapon clangs]

56
00:05:30.931 --> 00:05:32.232
[gasps softly]

57
00:05:34.702 --> 00:05:36.270
[screams] No!

58
00:05:36.403 --> 00:05:38.540
-[dramatic music playing]
-[Krem grunts]

59
00:05:44.211 --> 00:05:46.180
[device beeping rapidly]

60
00:05:47.114 --> 00:05:48.282
[man grunting in pain]

61
00:05:53.253 --> 00:05:54.556
[man groaning]

62
00:05:57.991 --> 00:05:59.960
Mm-hmm.

63
00:06:03.030 --> 00:06:05.432
[music echoes. distorts]

64
00:06:10.037 --> 00:06:12.206
[somber music playing]

65
00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:20.648
[breath trembling]

66
00:06:24.752 --> 00:06:28.222
-[engines thrumming]
-[distant chatter]

67
00:06:28.355 --> 00:06:30.725
[laid-back
jazzy pop music playing]

68
00:06:30.859 --> 00:06:32.359
[sighs]

69
00:06:33.628 --> 00:06:34.662
[barks]

70
00:06:34.796 --> 00:06:37.397
-[indistinct chatter]
-[alien chitters]

71
00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:43.738
I. Kara Zor-El.

72
00:06:43.872 --> 00:06:48.776
of inebriated mind. body.

73
00:06:48.910 --> 00:06:51.044
and. uh... spirit...

74
00:06:51.178 --> 00:06:53.715
I hereby declare...

75
00:06:55.517 --> 00:06:57.852
that 23 will be
the best year yet.

76
00:06:58.318 --> 00:06:59.486
But let's be honest. babe.

77
00:06:59.621 --> 00:07:02.022
it's not a very high bar
to clear.

78
00:07:06.159 --> 00:07:07.461
[coughs]

79
00:07:07.929 --> 00:07:09.062
-Okay...
-[barks]

80
00:07:10.364 --> 00:07:11.666
Should we just move here?

81
00:07:11.799 --> 00:07:14.334
Maybe we're meant to be
red sun folks. you know?

82
00:07:14.468 --> 00:07:18.405
The kinds who feel things like
a punch in the face

83
00:07:18.540 --> 00:07:21.241
and. like. shots of. like.
whatever this is.

84
00:07:23.143 --> 00:07:24.546
It's really good. you know?

85
00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:28.448
Maybe this is home.

86
00:07:34.187 --> 00:07:35.557
[machinery clicks on]

87
00:07:35.690 --> 00:07:37.825
["Catch These Fists" by Wet Leg
playing over speakers]

88
00:07:45.198 --> 00:07:46.300
[chokes sharply]

89
00:07:53.340 --> 00:07:55.944
[alien rumbles]

90
00:07:56.343 --> 00:07:57.512
Not gonna happen.

91
00:07:58.813 --> 00:08:00.648
[music continues inside]

92
00:08:17.331 --> 00:08:18.498
Attention.

93
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:21.869
[shouts] Attention!

94
00:08:24.672 --> 00:08:27.107
-[music stops]
-[dog growling]

95
00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:28.509
Seriously?

96
00:08:28.643 --> 00:08:31.079
I am Ruthye Marye Knoll
of the Danastia Clan.

97
00:08:31.278 --> 00:08:32.914
And I come here
with one purpose.

98
00:08:33.047 --> 00:08:34.381
-[dog growls]
-Man.

99
00:08:34.515 --> 00:08:36.149
To seek revenge against
Krem of the Yellow Hills...

100
00:08:36.283 --> 00:08:37.552
[patrons murmuring]

101
00:08:37.685 --> 00:08:39.319
...a Brigand who has
trespassed onto our planet.

102
00:08:39.453 --> 00:08:41.355
murdered my innocent
and honorable family

103
00:08:41.488 --> 00:08:43.323
-in cold blood.
-Rough.

104
00:08:43.457 --> 00:08:45.526
Krem's ship was destroyed.
and I believe

105
00:08:45.660 --> 00:08:47.294
he's still searching for
a passage off our planet.

106
00:08:47.427 --> 00:08:49.097
I will need a skilled tracker.

107
00:08:49.229 --> 00:08:50.598
who can help me locate
this monster

108
00:08:50.732 --> 00:08:53.001
-before he escapes.
-Dude. no.

109
00:08:53.133 --> 00:08:55.937
I don't-- I don't have
my powers here. all right?

110
00:08:56.070 --> 00:08:57.905
-[Ruthye] I will do the rest...
-Not my monkeys.

111
00:08:58.039 --> 00:08:59.206
Not my circus.

112
00:08:59.339 --> 00:09:00.842
...ending his life
to avenge my family.

113
00:09:03.911 --> 00:09:05.245
In exchange...

114
00:09:07.015 --> 00:09:08.683
I offer you my family sword.

115
00:09:09.383 --> 00:09:11.919
Made by the hands
of my father. Elias Knoll.

116
00:09:12.053 --> 00:09:13.153
[patrons murmuring]

117
00:09:13.286 --> 00:09:14.656
The blade will be
provided to you

118
00:09:14.789 --> 00:09:16.591
after I use it
to take Krem's life.

119
00:09:19.027 --> 00:09:20.327
It's not our problem.

120
00:09:20.460 --> 00:09:23.196
-Elias Knoll. you say?
-Yes.

121
00:09:24.899 --> 00:09:27.501
A child of your size expects
to wield such a weapon?

122
00:09:27.635 --> 00:09:28.736
[Ruthye] I am no child.

123
00:09:28.870 --> 00:09:30.872
I had my thirteenth turn
this past harvest.

124
00:09:31.005 --> 00:09:33.373
[bar patron]
Ah. but taking on a Brigand?

125
00:09:33.875 --> 00:09:36.644
-Impossible.
-Oh. that might be a problem.

126
00:09:36.778 --> 00:09:39.914
You will need someone of
enormous power to defeat Krem.

127
00:09:40.380 --> 00:09:41.348
I shall do the job myself.

128
00:09:41.481 --> 00:09:42.784
[alien growling]

129
00:09:48.422 --> 00:09:52.325
-Hey!
-[roars]

130
00:09:52.459 --> 00:09:53.594
-[grunts angrily]
-[clears throat]

131
00:09:53.728 --> 00:09:54.996
-[Kara] Mm-mm.
-[grunts]

132
00:09:55.129 --> 00:09:58.198
Hold this. All right. just...
Let me talk to him.

133
00:10:02.269 --> 00:10:04.672
[whistles] It's not too late.

134
00:10:04.806 --> 00:10:06.373
[alien growling]

135
00:10:06.507 --> 00:10:09.342
Let's not... be a jerk.

136
00:10:09.744 --> 00:10:11.913
Just... Just give me back
the sword-- Whoa.

137
00:10:13.648 --> 00:10:15.282
-...and we can move on.
-[alien growling angrily]

138
00:10:15.415 --> 00:10:17.451
You don't steal
from a little kid

139
00:10:17.585 --> 00:10:19.854
who just lost her parents.
Like. that's--

140
00:10:20.287 --> 00:10:22.156
Man. that's so clearly
over the line

141
00:10:22.289 --> 00:10:23.891
of acceptable behavior.

142
00:10:27.662 --> 00:10:29.797
You could at least
help her find the...

143
00:10:30.698 --> 00:10:31.566
God.

144
00:10:31.699 --> 00:10:33.400
...find the shithead
who killed them.

145
00:10:33.534 --> 00:10:34.535
and then you can get
the sword.

146
00:10:34.669 --> 00:10:35.903
like. fair and square.

147
00:10:36.037 --> 00:10:37.638
[grumbles angrily]

148
00:10:37.772 --> 00:10:39.807
Oh. you think
I'm talking too much?

149
00:10:39.941 --> 00:10:40.942
No problem.

150
00:10:41.976 --> 00:10:43.144
I can talk less.

151
00:10:43.644 --> 00:10:44.879
[creature bellows]

152
00:10:45.012 --> 00:10:47.048
[tense music playing]

153
00:10:47.181 --> 00:10:48.716
[Kara grunting softly]

154
00:10:50.051 --> 00:10:51.953
Okay. that was...
that was less talking.

155
00:10:52.720 --> 00:10:54.055
How do you like that?

156
00:10:54.188 --> 00:10:55.690
Oh. God! There it is. Wow.

157
00:10:55.990 --> 00:10:57.324
Okay.

158
00:10:57.457 --> 00:10:59.761
It's actually. like. a really
beautiful piece of silverware.

159
00:10:59.894 --> 00:11:01.261
[alien grunts]

160
00:11:07.869 --> 00:11:09.971
[laughs weakly]
Hey. look. I'm bleeding.

161
00:11:10.938 --> 00:11:11.873
Whoa!

162
00:11:13.306 --> 00:11:14.742
Whoa. what the fu--?

163
00:11:16.711 --> 00:11:18.746
Oh. you're an angry fella.
aren't you?

164
00:11:18.880 --> 00:11:21.048
[alien growling aggressively]

165
00:11:28.923 --> 00:11:29.857
[Kara yelps]

166
00:11:31.424 --> 00:11:32.794
[choking]

167
00:11:32.927 --> 00:11:34.762
[roars]

168
00:11:34.896 --> 00:11:37.297
Easy. Okay. Okay!
Give me a second.

169
00:11:37.430 --> 00:11:38.533
I'm a little...
I'm a little winded.

170
00:11:39.366 --> 00:11:40.467
No. no. no. no. no.

171
00:11:40.601 --> 00:11:41.969
[barking. snarling]

172
00:11:42.469 --> 00:11:43.604
Argh!

173
00:11:45.706 --> 00:11:47.975
[barking. snarling]

174
00:11:48.109 --> 00:11:50.211
[alien bellows in pain]

175
00:11:50.343 --> 00:11:52.079
-[barking]
-[growling angrily]

176
00:11:53.413 --> 00:11:54.481
[groans]

177
00:11:54.615 --> 00:11:56.050
-[thud]
-[Kara exhales]

178
00:11:58.485 --> 00:11:59.954
-[weapon thuds]
-[Kara] Whew.

179
00:12:00.353 --> 00:12:01.488
[alien coughing]

180
00:12:06.060 --> 00:12:07.595
[alien groaning]

181
00:12:13.668 --> 00:12:15.102
Believe this is yours.

182
00:12:19.472 --> 00:12:20.608
Thank you.

183
00:12:23.476 --> 00:12:24.712
I need to go to bed.

184
00:12:25.947 --> 00:12:26.914
[coughs]

185
00:12:28.850 --> 00:12:30.952
["Silver Lining"
by Rilo Kiley playing]

186
00:12:31.085 --> 00:12:32.587
[Kara groans softly]

187
00:12:34.322 --> 00:12:35.957
Stop. Stop.

188
00:12:38.092 --> 00:12:39.760
[dog whines]

189
00:12:40.995 --> 00:12:42.462
[Kara sighs]

190
00:12:47.235 --> 00:12:48.870
[exhales heavily]

191
00:12:50.972 --> 00:12:51.906
Oh.

192
00:12:53.241 --> 00:12:54.374
Um...

193
00:13:00.214 --> 00:13:01.249
Ow!

194
00:13:01.682 --> 00:13:04.384
Oh... [scoffs]

195
00:13:06.053 --> 00:13:06.988
Ugh.

196
00:13:08.155 --> 00:13:09.690
[sighs]

197
00:13:20.735 --> 00:13:22.370
<i>Hi! Hi. Finally got you.</i>

198
00:13:22.502 --> 00:13:24.839
Mm-hmm. It's my lucky day!

199
00:13:24.972 --> 00:13:27.041
<i>Still. uh...</i>
<i>still celebrating. huh?</i>

200
00:13:27.174 --> 00:13:28.342
Yeah. What do you want?

201
00:13:28.475 --> 00:13:31.112
<i>I was just... Just wanted</i>
<i>to touch base about</i>

202
00:13:31.245 --> 00:13:32.647
<i>when you think</i>
<i>you might be coming back.</i>

203
00:13:33.247 --> 00:13:34.248
No idea.

204
00:13:34.382 --> 00:13:35.850
<i>Kara. I'm just worried that...</i>

205
00:13:35.983 --> 00:13:37.718
<i>if you keep going off-planet</i>
<i>like this.</i>

206
00:13:37.852 --> 00:13:39.120
<i>you're never gonna find</i>
<i>your stride here.</i>

207
00:13:39.253 --> 00:13:40.221
<i>in Metropolis.</i>

208
00:13:40.354 --> 00:13:41.722
-[banging on door]
-Hold on.

209
00:13:41.856 --> 00:13:43.791
<i>I'm worried you might never</i>
<i>find your people.</i>

210
00:13:45.059 --> 00:13:48.596
Mm. That's the thing. Clark.
I have no people.

211
00:13:49.263 --> 00:13:50.497
<i>I know that.</i>

212
00:13:50.631 --> 00:13:52.733
<i>I just mean maybe if you spent</i>
<i>a little more time here.</i>

213
00:13:52.867 --> 00:13:54.368
<i>you might feel more at home.</i>

214
00:13:54.501 --> 00:13:57.238
-[banging on door continues]
-Hold on! Uh. I gotta go.

215
00:13:57.371 --> 00:13:59.273
<i>Okay. Just. um. give me a call</i>
<i>and let me know--</i>

216
00:13:59.407 --> 00:14:00.508
Good talk. Bye.

217
00:14:00.641 --> 00:14:01.842
[screen powers down]

218
00:14:01.976 --> 00:14:03.476
-[banging continues]
-[shouts] Hold on!

219
00:14:05.947 --> 00:14:08.115
I am Ruthye Marye Knoll
of the Danastia Clan.

220
00:14:08.783 --> 00:14:09.984
And I come here
to seek revenge--

221
00:14:10.117 --> 00:14:11.886
Yeah. some guy named Cream.
Yeah.

222
00:14:12.019 --> 00:14:13.754
You already hit me
with this pitch.

223
00:14:13.888 --> 00:14:16.023
So. what. you're going...

224
00:14:17.490 --> 00:14:18.993
You're door-to-door now?

225
00:14:19.126 --> 00:14:21.963
Look. I would love
to help you. but I can't.

226
00:14:22.096 --> 00:14:24.432
So. onto the next door
with you.

227
00:14:24.565 --> 00:14:25.900
[clothing unzips]

228
00:14:26.033 --> 00:14:28.936
Now. if you'll excuse me.
I really need to pee.

229
00:14:29.070 --> 00:14:30.137
Okay.

230
00:14:30.271 --> 00:14:32.106
-[liquid trickling]
-[Kara exhales heavily]

231
00:14:45.485 --> 00:14:46.988
-Was your ship attacked?
-Oh. my God.

232
00:14:49.256 --> 00:14:51.125
Wait! Please!

233
00:14:51.792 --> 00:14:54.161
Look. last night you stood up
for the righteous.

234
00:14:54.295 --> 00:14:55.495
The just.

235
00:14:55.629 --> 00:14:56.797
Look... [sighs]

236
00:14:57.431 --> 00:14:58.966
If you think I'm gonna
lead you on the mountains

237
00:14:59.100 --> 00:15:01.902
through some sort of...
revenge plot.

238
00:15:02.036 --> 00:15:05.606
turning you into
a psychotic... child murderer.

239
00:15:05.740 --> 00:15:08.776
then you must be. as they say.
"on glue."

240
00:15:10.344 --> 00:15:11.879
[chokes] Ew.

241
00:15:12.013 --> 00:15:14.248
[suspenseful music playing]

242
00:15:16.017 --> 00:15:17.618
[Brigands conversing
indistinctly]

243
00:15:26.961 --> 00:15:29.563
[speaking alien language]
Shall we take Elias' daughter?

244
00:15:30.031 --> 00:15:32.400
The cells are packed solid.
aren't they?

245
00:15:32.533 --> 00:15:33.634
[machinery whirrs. sparks]

246
00:15:35.703 --> 00:15:38.139
What do you think
of my new ship?

247
00:15:38.439 --> 00:15:39.573
[both laughing]

248
00:15:41.776 --> 00:15:42.877
[in English] Come on. man.

249
00:15:43.010 --> 00:15:44.945
We gotta be
back up in the sky ASAP.

250
00:15:45.346 --> 00:15:46.947
Krem deserves
what is coming to him.

251
00:15:48.482 --> 00:15:50.885
You go round driven by "deserve"
and you'll end up...

252
00:15:51.552 --> 00:15:52.686
very unhappy.

253
00:16:01.195 --> 00:16:02.563
[growls. barks]

254
00:16:04.065 --> 00:16:05.800
-Krypto!
-[continues barking]

255
00:16:05.933 --> 00:16:07.701
-[Ruthye] Krem. That's him.
-What the--? Hey!

256
00:16:07.835 --> 00:16:09.070
They're taking your ship
off the planet.

257
00:16:10.204 --> 00:16:11.305
[Kara] Krypto!

258
00:16:15.142 --> 00:16:16.811
No! Krypto!

259
00:16:17.678 --> 00:16:18.846
No!

260
00:16:20.614 --> 00:16:23.150
[Krypto whining]

261
00:16:30.491 --> 00:16:32.493
Hey. Hey. buddy.

262
00:16:33.094 --> 00:16:35.162
It's gonna be okay. Okay?

263
00:16:36.597 --> 00:16:38.666
[somber music playing]

264
00:16:47.975 --> 00:16:50.111
[healer speaking
alien language]

265
00:16:54.715 --> 00:16:56.150
[Ruthye. in English]
A Brigandian toxin

266
00:16:56.283 --> 00:16:57.118
known as Reddimeir.

267
00:16:57.251 --> 00:16:59.920
She says it paralyzes
the host slowly.

268
00:17:00.054 --> 00:17:01.755
and I'm sorry. but painfully.

269
00:17:01.889 --> 00:17:03.257
before eventually...

270
00:17:04.058 --> 00:17:05.192
stopping the heart.

271
00:17:06.694 --> 00:17:07.862
What can I do?

272
00:17:07.995 --> 00:17:09.730
[healer continues speaking
alien language]

273
00:17:10.631 --> 00:17:11.832
[in English] What? What is it?

274
00:17:13.568 --> 00:17:14.735
She says it's more difficult

275
00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:16.637
since Krem escaped
off the planet.

276
00:17:16.770 --> 00:17:18.806
Moving him
would risk accelerating

277
00:17:18.939 --> 00:17:20.509
the effects of the toxin.

278
00:17:21.041 --> 00:17:22.977
The Brigands carry
the antidote on their person.

279
00:17:25.514 --> 00:17:28.349
They use it
as an interrogation tactic.

280
00:17:28.482 --> 00:17:31.285
Dangling relief
in exchange for money.

281
00:17:31.752 --> 00:17:34.288
information.
whatever they're after.

282
00:17:34.421 --> 00:17:36.690
[continues speaking
alien language]

283
00:17:38.792 --> 00:17:39.793
[in English]
Without the antidote

284
00:17:39.927 --> 00:17:41.162
there's nothing she can do.

285
00:17:42.564 --> 00:17:43.731
How long does he have?

286
00:17:43.864 --> 00:17:45.766
[speaks alien language]

287
00:17:45.900 --> 00:17:47.268
[in English]
Three moon raises.

288
00:17:48.836 --> 00:17:51.238
Okay. Three days.

289
00:17:53.107 --> 00:17:56.744
Hey. Hey.
I'm gonna go now.

290
00:17:57.711 --> 00:17:59.480
[Krypto whines softly]

291
00:18:00.381 --> 00:18:03.784
And you-- You cannot
freaking give up on me.

292
00:18:05.654 --> 00:18:07.221
Home is
wherever you are. buddy.

293
00:18:10.824 --> 00:18:11.926
[Kara kisses Krypto]

294
00:18:13.294 --> 00:18:14.295
[Kara sighs]

295
00:18:15.696 --> 00:18:18.032
[melancholy music playing]

296
00:18:19.833 --> 00:18:21.869
Are you going after Krem
for the antidote?

297
00:18:22.604 --> 00:18:23.672
You could help me.

298
00:18:23.804 --> 00:18:25.206
No. we could help each other.

299
00:18:25.339 --> 00:18:28.842
You for the antidote.
and me to kill him.

300
00:18:29.743 --> 00:18:32.713
Look. I'm... I'm sorry...

301
00:18:33.247 --> 00:18:34.516
about what happened
to your family.

302
00:18:34.649 --> 00:18:36.217
Okay? I am. So he'll suffer.

303
00:18:36.350 --> 00:18:37.718
Suffer?
No. he needs to be killed.

304
00:18:37.851 --> 00:18:40.020
[Kara] Ruthye. your revenge
is not going to get in the way

305
00:18:40.154 --> 00:18:41.789
of me saving my dog.

306
00:18:43.390 --> 00:18:46.026
Okay. just... like. just
stay here and look after him.

307
00:19:01.809 --> 00:19:02.977
Okay.

308
00:19:03.844 --> 00:19:05.379
One...

309
00:19:05.513 --> 00:19:06.615
Two...

310
00:19:07.181 --> 00:19:09.783
Three... moon raises.

311
00:19:11.352 --> 00:19:13.854
72 hours. buddy.

312
00:19:13.988 --> 00:19:17.291
[melancholy music continues]

313
00:19:31.972 --> 00:19:33.508
[Kara speaks Kryptonian]
Who are you?

314
00:19:39.847 --> 00:19:41.448
[sighs]

315
00:19:44.686 --> 00:19:46.987
[engine rumbling]

316
00:19:57.031 --> 00:19:59.433
["Satin in a Coffin"
by Modest Mouse playing]

317
00:19:59.567 --> 00:20:02.704
[speaks alien language
in impatient tone]

318
00:20:03.571 --> 00:20:04.673
[in English] He basically
said. "Welcome aboard.

319
00:20:04.805 --> 00:20:05.774
Please watch your step."

320
00:20:05.906 --> 00:20:08.142
Yeah. sure he did.

321
00:20:21.723 --> 00:20:24.191
[passenger grumbling]

322
00:20:25.326 --> 00:20:27.328
[alien squealing. trilling]

323
00:20:32.399 --> 00:20:34.602
[passenger grunting. gurgling]

324
00:20:34.736 --> 00:20:35.869
[Kara] Gum?

325
00:20:42.744 --> 00:20:46.146
Maybe give us all a break
from that hookah thingy.

326
00:20:46.280 --> 00:20:48.282
[passenger grumbles]

327
00:20:48.415 --> 00:20:49.551
Okay.

328
00:20:50.217 --> 00:20:52.386
-Comfy?
-[gasps startledly]

329
00:20:55.022 --> 00:20:56.190
You got a clue
what I'm saying?

330
00:20:57.391 --> 00:20:59.393
Do I look like an idiot
to you?

331
00:21:00.829 --> 00:21:01.895
Debatable.

332
00:21:02.029 --> 00:21:03.531
[Ruthye] I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to.

333
00:21:03.665 --> 00:21:05.299
I was just trying
to get through to my seat.

334
00:21:05.432 --> 00:21:07.669
-It was an accident.
-Oh. freakin' Ruthye.

335
00:21:08.035 --> 00:21:09.604
[alien chittering agitatedly]

336
00:21:13.474 --> 00:21:14.875
-[alien growling]
-[Ruthye] Ow.

337
00:21:15.008 --> 00:21:16.009
[Kara screeches]

338
00:21:16.143 --> 00:21:18.379
[alien screeches. exclaims]

339
00:21:18.513 --> 00:21:21.181
-[Kara screeches]
-[alien grumbles softly]

340
00:21:24.118 --> 00:21:25.520
You put your bag on the floor
at her feet.

341
00:21:25.653 --> 00:21:28.021
which is calling her mother
a whore.

342
00:21:28.556 --> 00:21:31.793
Okay. why aren't you
with Krypto?

343
00:21:31.925 --> 00:21:33.327
I'm searching for Krem myself.

344
00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:37.498
I think I was pretty clear
when I said no to that plan.

345
00:21:39.066 --> 00:21:40.234
Excuse me. can you move over

346
00:21:40.367 --> 00:21:41.736
so I can sit
next to my friend?

347
00:21:41.870 --> 00:21:43.904
Oh. your friend. Absolutely.

348
00:21:44.037 --> 00:21:45.272
She's not my fr...
You're not my friend.

349
00:21:45.406 --> 00:21:46.373
Yes. I am.

350
00:21:48.409 --> 00:21:49.376
Okay.

351
00:21:50.911 --> 00:21:53.180
-What's my name?
-What?

352
00:21:53.313 --> 00:21:55.182
-[ship judders]
-[passengers exclaiming]

353
00:21:55.449 --> 00:21:57.951
[speaks alien language]
What did you hit now. Lloyd?

354
00:22:00.954 --> 00:22:03.290
[foreboding music playing]

355
00:22:14.468 --> 00:22:15.537
[Ruthye. in English]
Who are they?

356
00:22:15.670 --> 00:22:16.671
What do they want?

357
00:22:16.805 --> 00:22:18.138
[Kara] Sklarian Raiders.

358
00:22:18.272 --> 00:22:20.040
They're like tech pirates.

359
00:22:20.675 --> 00:22:22.577
They want the bus.
they want the fuel.

360
00:22:22.710 --> 00:22:23.611
they want the engine.

361
00:22:23.745 --> 00:22:25.814
Look away. Lloyd.
Look away. Look away.

362
00:22:26.447 --> 00:22:28.683
My guess is they want
to rob us all blind first.

363
00:22:30.117 --> 00:22:31.251
[chitters]

364
00:22:33.187 --> 00:22:35.189
[scanner humming]

365
00:22:46.701 --> 00:22:48.570
[grunts discontentedly]

366
00:22:49.904 --> 00:22:51.071
[yelps]

367
00:22:53.808 --> 00:22:55.108
Noted.

368
00:22:55.242 --> 00:22:57.244
I knew I should have
called in sick today. Lloyd.

369
00:22:58.312 --> 00:23:00.080
[robots continue prowling]

370
00:23:03.250 --> 00:23:04.084
[speaks alien language]
The watch.

371
00:23:24.438 --> 00:23:26.741
[in English] No. she doesn't--
You know. she doesn't--

372
00:23:26.875 --> 00:23:28.676
Ruthye. Ruthye. let go.

373
00:23:28.810 --> 00:23:31.713
Ruthye. let go. Let go.

374
00:23:33.781 --> 00:23:36.684
[whispers] Between you and me.
the sword...

375
00:23:36.818 --> 00:23:38.485
It's not worth much. you know.
See--

376
00:23:47.361 --> 00:23:49.162
I have a plan.

377
00:23:51.766 --> 00:23:52.800
Kind of.

378
00:23:53.902 --> 00:23:55.537
Hey!

379
00:23:55.970 --> 00:23:57.605
You ladies wanna trade?

380
00:23:58.438 --> 00:23:59.874
'Cause I would love
that watch and sword back.

381
00:24:00.008 --> 00:24:02.744
and I'm pretty sure that
you would be interested...

382
00:24:02.877 --> 00:24:04.177
in this.

383
00:24:04.979 --> 00:24:06.514
Oh. sorry. wrong pocket.

384
00:24:06.648 --> 00:24:07.715
In this.

385
00:24:09.149 --> 00:24:10.952
["Smile" by Wolf Alice playing]

386
00:24:11.084 --> 00:24:12.754
[exhales sharply]

387
00:24:15.857 --> 00:24:17.559
[electricity crackling]

388
00:24:17.692 --> 00:24:19.761
Whoa. Oh. shit.

389
00:24:24.364 --> 00:24:27.301
Uh. just getting my sea legs.

390
00:24:30.404 --> 00:24:32.406
[Kara grunting]

391
00:24:35.342 --> 00:24:37.177
-[alien exclaims]
-Shit.

392
00:24:40.180 --> 00:24:41.281
[alien exclaims]

393
00:24:41.415 --> 00:24:43.051
[Kara] Okay.
this is unpleasant.

394
00:24:43.183 --> 00:24:45.218
[squelching]

395
00:24:50.123 --> 00:24:51.793
[Kara grunting]

396
00:25:05.974 --> 00:25:07.240
[groans]

397
00:25:11.244 --> 00:25:14.247
[whispers] Hey. Hey. uh...

398
00:25:14.381 --> 00:25:16.618
How... How close are we
to a yellow sun?

399
00:25:16.751 --> 00:25:20.588
[both converse
in alien language]

400
00:25:21.488 --> 00:25:23.390
[distant creaking. thudding]

401
00:25:27.829 --> 00:25:29.530
[in English]
Can you get any closer?

402
00:25:29.664 --> 00:25:31.431
Yeah. sure. If I had
a friggin' engine

403
00:25:31.566 --> 00:25:34.501
or some balls.
but I have neither. So. no.

404
00:25:37.839 --> 00:25:40.173
Perfect. Um...

405
00:25:40.307 --> 00:25:41.576
[suspenseful music playing]

406
00:25:41.709 --> 00:25:43.645
[passenger screams
in distance]

407
00:25:45.212 --> 00:25:46.380
[coughs]

408
00:25:54.589 --> 00:25:55.923
Shhh.

409
00:25:56.057 --> 00:25:57.625
Ooh. this is gonna be bad.

410
00:25:57.759 --> 00:25:59.326
[straining]

411
00:26:01.194 --> 00:26:02.295
Come on.

412
00:26:16.844 --> 00:26:18.178
Oh. shi--

413
00:26:30.257 --> 00:26:32.960
[somber music playing]

414
00:27:09.097 --> 00:27:10.330
[footstep thuds]

415
00:27:11.199 --> 00:27:12.265
[grunting]

416
00:27:12.399 --> 00:27:14.869
[wondrous music playing]

417
00:27:31.485 --> 00:27:33.386
[laser fires]

418
00:27:49.704 --> 00:27:50.772
[speaks alien language]
She's flying towards the sun!

419
00:27:58.579 --> 00:28:01.348
[thrilling music playing]

420
00:28:32.280 --> 00:28:33.881
[lasers pulsing]

421
00:28:49.396 --> 00:28:51.766
[explosions. ship juddering]

422
00:28:54.635 --> 00:28:55.636
[speaking alien language]
We've lost our engines!

423
00:28:57.337 --> 00:28:58.873
Found them.

424
00:29:08.749 --> 00:29:10.918
["I've Got Trouble In Mind"
by the Limiñanas playing]

425
00:29:26.100 --> 00:29:28.468
[creature squealing]

426
00:29:33.875 --> 00:29:34.909
[in English]
When I asked for your help.

427
00:29:35.042 --> 00:29:36.611
I did not know
you were so capable.

428
00:29:36.744 --> 00:29:39.446
Yeah. You won the lottery.

429
00:29:39.580 --> 00:29:40.915
Why couldn't you do that
on my planet?

430
00:29:41.048 --> 00:29:43.351
I get my powers
from the yellow sun.

431
00:29:43.483 --> 00:29:46.453
The... red sun
makes me normal.

432
00:29:47.021 --> 00:29:48.522
Then why would you choose
to be under a red sun?

433
00:29:48.656 --> 00:29:50.124
Well. 'cause the whiskey
don't work so good

434
00:29:50.258 --> 00:29:51.391
when I'm like this.

435
00:29:52.526 --> 00:29:54.061
With abilities like that.

436
00:29:54.195 --> 00:29:55.663
you're sure to be able
to take on Krem.

437
00:29:55.796 --> 00:29:58.633
Enough! You're coming with me
to find Krem.

438
00:29:58.766 --> 00:30:01.836
Congratulations.
You wore me down.

439
00:30:03.470 --> 00:30:05.106
You were gonna do it
either way.

440
00:30:05.573 --> 00:30:07.141
At best
you'll end up kidnapped.

441
00:30:07.275 --> 00:30:09.076
At worst you'll screw it up
for the both of us.

442
00:30:09.210 --> 00:30:11.478
and... oh. I've got
to save my dog.

443
00:30:12.280 --> 00:30:14.447
Just do what I say.

444
00:30:14.582 --> 00:30:16.617
Keep quiet and don't die.

445
00:30:16.751 --> 00:30:18.953
There she is.
It's flying sun lady.

446
00:30:19.086 --> 00:30:20.721
Good job.
We kicked ass back there. huh?

447
00:30:20.855 --> 00:30:22.189
We make a good team. I think.

448
00:30:22.323 --> 00:30:23.758
We're wondering if you could
help us find the Brigands.

449
00:30:23.891 --> 00:30:24.892
Do you have any idea
where they are?

450
00:30:25.026 --> 00:30:26.160
No idea.

451
00:30:26.294 --> 00:30:28.162
But I bet those Sklarians
that you tied up on my bus

452
00:30:28.296 --> 00:30:29.630
probably do.

453
00:30:29.764 --> 00:30:31.399
See. that is an idea.

454
00:30:31.532 --> 00:30:34.201
Here's an even better idea:
Don't abandon your daughter.

455
00:30:38.873 --> 00:30:40.641
These taste like shit.
Um. okay.

456
00:30:41.842 --> 00:30:43.476
I really don't have time
for this. so...

457
00:30:43.611 --> 00:30:45.179
[brushes off hands]
...let's get to it.

458
00:30:46.881 --> 00:30:48.516
Oh. it's okay. Don't worry.

459
00:30:48.649 --> 00:30:50.450
I'll do the other side
to even it out...

460
00:30:50.584 --> 00:30:52.320
if you tell me
where to find Krem.

461
00:30:52.920 --> 00:30:54.255
And what will you give us
in return?

462
00:30:54.388 --> 00:30:55.423
Oh. that's a good question.

463
00:30:55.556 --> 00:30:57.124
-Um...
-[Ruthye crunches]

464
00:30:59.492 --> 00:31:00.962
An intact spinal cord.

465
00:31:01.529 --> 00:31:02.697
So you gonna talk or...

466
00:31:03.397 --> 00:31:04.699
[whispering in alien language]
Let her have him.

467
00:31:04.832 --> 00:31:06.534
Krem has the strength
of one thousand men.

468
00:31:06.667 --> 00:31:07.702
He'll tear
this little girl apart.

469
00:31:11.572 --> 00:31:13.140
[in English] He's on Bilquis.

470
00:31:16.077 --> 00:31:17.578
Nice try.
Bilquis's a dead planet.

471
00:31:17.712 --> 00:31:19.613
Dying. not dead.

472
00:31:19.747 --> 00:31:21.716
The atomic wars
brought destruction.

473
00:31:21.849 --> 00:31:23.617
Half the population is gone.

474
00:31:23.751 --> 00:31:26.387
And the remaining resources
have drawn filth.

475
00:31:26.520 --> 00:31:28.322
From every corner
of the galaxy.

476
00:31:28.756 --> 00:31:30.825
Filth. Like the Brigands.

477
00:31:30.958 --> 00:31:32.626
They scavenge for people.

478
00:31:34.362 --> 00:31:35.495
People?

479
00:31:38.265 --> 00:31:39.467
For girls.

480
00:31:40.334 --> 00:31:43.637
Girls to help them continue
their all-male race.

481
00:31:47.274 --> 00:31:48.342
Cool.

482
00:31:48.809 --> 00:31:49.910
[clicks tongue]

483
00:31:50.778 --> 00:31:52.380
So we're going to Bilquis.

484
00:31:52.513 --> 00:31:54.081
[tense music playing]

485
00:32:01.956 --> 00:32:03.991
All right.
let's take you shopping.

486
00:32:05.593 --> 00:32:06.827
Perfect.

487
00:32:11.565 --> 00:32:13.534
-Don't freak out.
-Why would I?

488
00:32:13.667 --> 00:32:14.835
[device powers up]

489
00:32:16.837 --> 00:32:18.472
-I'm not freaking out.
-You're not freaking out.

490
00:32:18.606 --> 00:32:20.007
I'm not freaking out!

491
00:32:20.141 --> 00:32:21.342
Seems to me
like you're freaking out.

492
00:32:21.475 --> 00:32:23.711
-I might be freaking out.
-Okay.

493
00:32:23.844 --> 00:32:25.546
[device powers down]

494
00:32:25.679 --> 00:32:26.814
Good.

495
00:32:26.947 --> 00:32:28.215
Now you won't die.

496
00:32:28.783 --> 00:32:30.818
[suspenseful music playing]

497
00:32:43.697 --> 00:32:45.066
[Ruthye] Whoa!

498
00:32:46.567 --> 00:32:48.702
[grunting]

499
00:32:53.007 --> 00:32:54.008
[device powers down]

500
00:32:54.141 --> 00:32:55.576
You could have
done that sooner.

501
00:32:55.709 --> 00:32:56.877
Yep.

502
00:33:04.685 --> 00:33:06.687
-On your planet...
-Earth.

503
00:33:07.488 --> 00:33:08.989
[Ruthye] Do others on Earth
have powers like you?

504
00:33:09.123 --> 00:33:11.526
No. it's a pretty small group
of two.

505
00:33:11.659 --> 00:33:12.793
[Ruthye] Who's the other one?

506
00:33:12.927 --> 00:33:14.328
They call him Superman.

507
00:33:15.564 --> 00:33:16.864
I call him Clark.
He's my cousin.

508
00:33:17.665 --> 00:33:19.233
And you are Superwoman?

509
00:33:19.366 --> 00:33:20.868
I'm Supergirl.

510
00:33:21.502 --> 00:33:23.838
Are you considerably younger
than he is?

511
00:33:23.971 --> 00:33:26.941
[sighs] There's. like.
ten years. give or take.

512
00:33:27.074 --> 00:33:28.909
How come he's a man?
I mean. you're--

513
00:33:29.043 --> 00:33:30.512
[man] Move it! Out of the way.

514
00:33:30.644 --> 00:33:32.346
[alien chitters]

515
00:33:33.347 --> 00:33:34.648
[man laughing]

516
00:33:34.782 --> 00:33:36.250
Let's find some Brigands.

517
00:33:36.817 --> 00:33:38.819
-[piano playing]
-[indistinct chatter]

518
00:33:40.955 --> 00:33:43.190
[performer singing
indistinctly]

519
00:33:43.324 --> 00:33:45.392
[stops singing]

520
00:33:47.461 --> 00:33:48.696
[door creaks shut]

521
00:33:48.829 --> 00:33:51.098
[patrons fall silent]

522
00:33:55.736 --> 00:33:56.904
Thank you.

523
00:33:59.608 --> 00:34:01.208
[music resumes]

524
00:34:01.976 --> 00:34:03.210
<i>♪ Tall and tan</i>
<i>And young and lovely ♪</i>

525
00:34:03.344 --> 00:34:05.012
[speaks alien language]
Sorry. we are a bit backed up.

526
00:34:05.246 --> 00:34:07.348
[singer] <i>♪ The girl from Ipanema</i>
<i>Goes walking ♪</i>

527
00:34:07.481 --> 00:34:09.150
Hi.

528
00:34:09.283 --> 00:34:14.455
[singer] <i>♪ And when she passes</i>
<i>Each one she passes goes "Ah!" ♪</i>

529
00:34:14.722 --> 00:34:17.258
[tense music playing]

530
00:34:17.992 --> 00:34:20.094
[singer] <i>♪ But I watch her</i>
<i>So sadly... ♪</i>

531
00:34:20.227 --> 00:34:21.162
[exhales]

532
00:34:22.730 --> 00:34:24.633
I know she's worth a lot
'round here.

533
00:34:24.765 --> 00:34:25.933
I'm aware.

534
00:34:27.234 --> 00:34:30.639
Let me have her
and you can walk out alive.

535
00:34:30.771 --> 00:34:32.239
Tempting.

536
00:34:34.141 --> 00:34:36.777
But just
switching subjects here.

537
00:34:37.244 --> 00:34:38.913
Do you have any information
on the Brigands?

538
00:34:39.446 --> 00:34:41.782
That sort of information's
gonna cost ya.

539
00:34:45.085 --> 00:34:46.253
I'll tell you what.

540
00:34:48.989 --> 00:34:50.224
I'll arm-wrestle you for her.

541
00:34:51.292 --> 00:34:52.159
Seriously.

542
00:34:52.293 --> 00:34:53.562
You win
and you can have us both.

543
00:34:53.694 --> 00:34:55.062
I win...

544
00:34:55.664 --> 00:34:57.464
and you can tell us
where the Brigands are.

545
00:34:57.599 --> 00:34:59.200
[patrons chuckle]

546
00:35:03.137 --> 00:35:05.105
-Deal.
-Deal.

547
00:35:11.946 --> 00:35:14.715
[thuggish patron]
How about you play with me?

548
00:35:19.920 --> 00:35:21.889
[drink containers clatter]

549
00:35:23.857 --> 00:35:25.192
[can clatters]

550
00:35:26.661 --> 00:35:27.828
[grunts expectantly]

551
00:35:34.969 --> 00:35:36.337
You ready?

552
00:35:36.837 --> 00:35:38.640
-[snap]
-[thug yells]

553
00:35:38.772 --> 00:35:41.008
[weapons powering up]

554
00:35:41.842 --> 00:35:43.344
[thug groaning]

555
00:35:43.477 --> 00:35:44.445
Okay.

556
00:35:46.213 --> 00:35:49.750
Okay. this does not look like
this is gonna end well.

557
00:35:50.552 --> 00:35:52.520
For you guys. I mean.

558
00:35:53.754 --> 00:35:54.922
Anybody want to leave?

559
00:35:55.823 --> 00:35:57.891
No? Okay.

560
00:35:58.025 --> 00:36:00.094
Ah. let's not hurt
the merchandise.

561
00:36:00.595 --> 00:36:01.929
Ruthye. sit down over there.

562
00:36:02.062 --> 00:36:03.897
[thug 2] I'll kill you.

563
00:36:06.735 --> 00:36:07.901
Keep playing.

564
00:36:08.603 --> 00:36:11.105
You know.
It's like the <i>Titanic.</i> Yeah.

565
00:36:11.238 --> 00:36:13.874
[singer] <i>♪ Heaven</i>
<i>I'm in heaven ♪</i>

566
00:36:15.109 --> 00:36:17.646
Okay. boys.
Fingers on triggers?

567
00:36:17.778 --> 00:36:19.413
<i>♪ And my heart beats</i>
<i>So that I can hardly speak ♪</i>

568
00:36:19.547 --> 00:36:20.914
Yeah? Okay. Let's go.

569
00:36:21.048 --> 00:36:25.419
[singer] ♪ <i>And I seem to find</i>
<i>The happiness I seek ♪</i>

570
00:36:25.553 --> 00:36:27.354
[all yelling. grunting]

571
00:36:27.488 --> 00:36:29.591
[singer]
<i>♪ When we're out together ♪</i>

572
00:36:29.724 --> 00:36:33.528
<i>♪ Dancing cheek to cheek ♪</i>

573
00:36:34.194 --> 00:36:39.433
<i>♪ Heaven. I'm in heaven ♪</i>

574
00:36:40.100 --> 00:36:42.970
<i>♪ And the cares</i>
<i>That hung around me ♪</i>

575
00:36:43.103 --> 00:36:45.239
<i>♪ Through the week... ♪</i>

576
00:36:45.707 --> 00:36:48.442
How was that discreet?
You broke that man's arm.

577
00:36:48.576 --> 00:36:50.712
Okay. I'm...
Look. I'm... I'm sorry.

578
00:36:50.844 --> 00:36:52.313
Okay? My dog's dying.

579
00:36:52.446 --> 00:36:53.447
so I don't really have
the patience

580
00:36:53.581 --> 00:36:56.016
that I should have right now.
Okay?

581
00:36:56.150 --> 00:36:58.520
[bar patrons
groaning. coughing]

582
00:36:59.953 --> 00:37:01.690
[chuckles]

583
00:37:01.822 --> 00:37:03.824
[continues applauding]

584
00:37:05.727 --> 00:37:06.827
Oh. you don't have to.

585
00:37:06.960 --> 00:37:08.429
No. no. no. no.
It's good. It's good.

586
00:37:08.563 --> 00:37:10.297
Oh. I didn't know that
you spoke the Common Tongue.

587
00:37:10.431 --> 00:37:11.365
Little.

588
00:37:16.970 --> 00:37:18.573
-Mareck.
-Mar... Mareck.

589
00:37:19.306 --> 00:37:20.374
Bomar.

590
00:37:20.508 --> 00:37:23.477
Well. we're actually here
looking for somebody.

591
00:37:23.611 --> 00:37:26.380
You don't happen to know
any Brigands? Do you?

592
00:37:27.181 --> 00:37:28.882
[objects clattering]

593
00:37:29.718 --> 00:37:31.485
[tense music playing]

594
00:37:32.687 --> 00:37:34.355
[man growls]

595
00:37:37.792 --> 00:37:38.926
Shit.

596
00:37:39.993 --> 00:37:41.128
It's Lobo.

597
00:37:45.499 --> 00:37:46.735
-Who?
-[Kara] Keep quiet.

598
00:37:46.867 --> 00:37:48.469
No eye contact.

599
00:37:51.472 --> 00:37:53.173
He's an immortal
with a God complex.

600
00:37:53.307 --> 00:37:55.175
Killed off his entire planet.

601
00:37:55.309 --> 00:37:57.177
Not a fun guy. Hey.

602
00:37:59.146 --> 00:38:01.549
Three more of whatever
you call that shit.

603
00:38:03.083 --> 00:38:04.251
I'm looking for a Brigand.

604
00:38:04.385 --> 00:38:06.186
Goes by the name
of Drom Baxton.

605
00:38:06.320 --> 00:38:07.388
He's an ugly friggin' bastich.

606
00:38:07.522 --> 00:38:09.256
-He's looking for Brigands.
-No!

607
00:38:09.390 --> 00:38:11.925
Red mohawk. Dead left eye.

608
00:38:12.059 --> 00:38:13.193
[Lobo slurps]

609
00:38:13.862 --> 00:38:15.295
[glass shatters]

610
00:38:16.063 --> 00:38:17.866
[whispers] He's so rude.

611
00:38:18.432 --> 00:38:19.433
[speaks alien language]
Have you seen him?

612
00:38:19.801 --> 00:38:20.901
[in common tongue] No.

613
00:38:21.502 --> 00:38:24.271
I know he was here.
You're saying he wasn't?

614
00:38:24.405 --> 00:38:26.240
-I'm gonna go.
-Sit down.

615
00:38:28.041 --> 00:38:29.476
Are you calling me a liar?

616
00:38:34.348 --> 00:38:35.282
No.

617
00:38:38.318 --> 00:38:39.521
Well. I am.
[laughs wheezingly]

618
00:38:40.921 --> 00:38:42.456
But not about this.

619
00:38:44.291 --> 00:38:45.325
He's worth a lot of money.

620
00:38:45.459 --> 00:38:47.127
Take care of my whole year.

621
00:38:48.362 --> 00:38:49.997
-[grunts]
-[glass clatters]

622
00:38:50.832 --> 00:38:52.433
-Excuse me.
-Go away.

623
00:38:52.567 --> 00:38:54.368
I am Ruthye Marye Knoll
of the Danastia Clan.

624
00:38:54.501 --> 00:38:55.335
Who cares?

625
00:38:55.469 --> 00:38:57.371
And I come here
with one purpose.

626
00:38:57.504 --> 00:39:00.073
to seek revenge against
Krem of the Yellow Hills.

627
00:39:00.207 --> 00:39:02.209
We could help you
take on the Brigands.

628
00:39:02.342 --> 00:39:04.311
You're going to help me?

629
00:39:05.547 --> 00:39:07.816
Do you know
who you are speaking to?

630
00:39:08.248 --> 00:39:09.851
[Ruthye gasps faintly]

631
00:39:10.518 --> 00:39:12.152
Would you like to find out?

632
00:39:13.220 --> 00:39:14.856
Hi! We're just
a couple of girls

633
00:39:14.988 --> 00:39:18.192
from Metropolis. USA.

634
00:39:18.325 --> 00:39:19.493
We're doing a fun little tour.

635
00:39:19.627 --> 00:39:20.929
-Of space!
-[weapon sheathes]

636
00:39:21.061 --> 00:39:23.063
It's for my... my birthday.

637
00:39:23.565 --> 00:39:24.799
Yeah. we've been on.
what is it.

638
00:39:24.933 --> 00:39:27.067
like. three planets so far?

639
00:39:27.201 --> 00:39:29.303
And I'm exhausted. [giggles]

640
00:39:29.436 --> 00:39:32.339
You know?
Like. OMG. I had no idea

641
00:39:32.473 --> 00:39:34.809
that space was
so. like. vast and...

642
00:39:34.943 --> 00:39:36.210
[Lobo] Stop.

643
00:39:37.579 --> 00:39:40.280
You're hurting my head.
[slurps. grunts]

644
00:39:43.016 --> 00:39:45.118
You all have been
super useless.

645
00:39:45.920 --> 00:39:47.254
Happy birthday.

646
00:39:50.090 --> 00:39:51.726
-Useless.
-[door creaks. clatters]

647
00:39:53.460 --> 00:39:56.430
We know friend know Brigands.

648
00:39:57.732 --> 00:39:59.199
Our house. meet?

649
00:39:59.333 --> 00:40:02.737
We walk.
but not safe for Ruthye.

650
00:40:03.838 --> 00:40:05.305
Wear this?

651
00:40:05.439 --> 00:40:06.941
[tense music playing]

652
00:40:07.074 --> 00:40:10.010
Bomar get friend
and meet home.

653
00:40:15.315 --> 00:40:17.217
[indistinct discussion
in alien language]

654
00:40:33.166 --> 00:40:34.536
[Mareck. in common tongue]
Wait here.

655
00:40:38.238 --> 00:40:41.543
Girl is tired. Rest.

656
00:40:41.676 --> 00:40:43.477
When will Bomar be here
with your friend?

657
00:40:43.611 --> 00:40:44.646
Soon.

658
00:40:48.516 --> 00:40:50.450
So. is Superman like you?

659
00:40:51.619 --> 00:40:53.655
Grumpy? Rude?

660
00:40:53.788 --> 00:40:56.056
-You think I'm rude?
-Of course.

661
00:40:56.691 --> 00:40:58.191
Seems to be something
you do intentionally.

662
00:40:58.325 --> 00:41:00.528
-Okay.
-Is Superman not that way?

663
00:41:00.662 --> 00:41:02.095
[Kara] Clark? No.

664
00:41:02.229 --> 00:41:04.566
He's a freakin' nerd.

665
00:41:04.966 --> 00:41:06.099
Let's just say
we're not alike.

666
00:41:06.233 --> 00:41:08.268
-Because?
-I don't know.

667
00:41:08.402 --> 00:41:10.070
He sees the good in everyone.
and I see the truth.

668
00:41:10.203 --> 00:41:11.573
So you think he's naive?

669
00:41:11.706 --> 00:41:15.577
-No. but... He's young.
-But isn't he older than you?

670
00:41:15.710 --> 00:41:17.845
Yeah. but it's not his age
that makes him young.

671
00:41:17.979 --> 00:41:19.379
it's his heart.

672
00:41:19.514 --> 00:41:22.517
There are just some things
he never had to go through.

673
00:41:22.650 --> 00:41:25.753
So his heart is light.
you know?

674
00:41:25.887 --> 00:41:29.389
It's not like mine or Bomar's
or your--

675
00:41:38.866 --> 00:41:39.867
What's Earth like?

676
00:41:44.304 --> 00:41:46.139
I'm not really
from Earth. Ruthye.

677
00:41:47.775 --> 00:41:49.109
From another planet.

678
00:41:51.045 --> 00:41:52.179
Krypton.

679
00:41:55.783 --> 00:41:59.053
I thought everyone died
the day the core erupted.

680
00:41:59.453 --> 00:42:01.623
No. Krypton didn't die
in a day.

681
00:42:03.057 --> 00:42:04.525
The gods are not that kind.

682
00:42:05.994 --> 00:42:07.895
[thunder crackling]

683
00:42:09.363 --> 00:42:12.399
[Kara] <i>My father</i>
<i>and his brother Jor-El</i>

684
00:42:12.533 --> 00:42:15.335
<i>tried to warn the Council</i>
<i>of what was coming...</i>

685
00:42:16.303 --> 00:42:19.073
<i>but no one listened.</i>

686
00:42:19.206 --> 00:42:21.743
[unsettled music playing]

687
00:42:24.045 --> 00:42:26.480
[chandelier rattling]

688
00:42:29.550 --> 00:42:30.652
Mm.

689
00:42:32.820 --> 00:42:34.889
[speaking Kryptonian] Is it now?
I thought we had more time.

690
00:42:35.023 --> 00:42:37.925
So did I. but Krypton's core
is too unstable.

691
00:42:39.060 --> 00:42:40.293
It will explode in minutes.

692
00:42:40.695 --> 00:42:44.364
I have triggered
the force field. We need to go.

693
00:42:44.498 --> 00:42:46.000
-[wood splintering overhead]
-Alura!

694
00:42:46.134 --> 00:42:48.301
-Now!
-[exclaims]

695
00:42:54.542 --> 00:42:56.044
[all clamoring]

696
00:42:56.176 --> 00:42:57.879
Is that him?

697
00:43:00.313 --> 00:43:01.281
That is Kal-El.

698
00:43:01.448 --> 00:43:02.684
The sweet little boy

699
00:43:02.817 --> 00:43:04.484
your brother has declared
a conqueror of worlds.

700
00:43:09.023 --> 00:43:10.692
It's time.

701
00:43:11.125 --> 00:43:13.460
[people clamoring. screaming]

702
00:43:17.230 --> 00:43:19.701
[energy reverberating]

703
00:43:46.961 --> 00:43:49.864
[Kara. in common tongue]
<i>That was eight years</i>
<i>before I was born.</i>

704
00:43:49.997 --> 00:43:52.232
[somber music playing]

705
00:44:02.176 --> 00:44:05.345
[speaking Kryptonian]
Are we fools. Zor-El?

706
00:44:05.479 --> 00:44:08.683
Should we have listened
to your brother?

707
00:44:08.816 --> 00:44:11.652
We can't send our daughter...

708
00:44:11.786 --> 00:44:14.122
to another planet
to be some sort of god.

709
00:44:14.488 --> 00:44:16.490
We preserved all this
for a reason.

710
00:44:18.126 --> 00:44:22.563
We have to believe
there's a future here.

711
00:44:26.333 --> 00:44:28.669
[bright music playing]

712
00:44:28.803 --> 00:44:31.873
[Alura calls playfully]
Kara. where are you?

713
00:44:38.212 --> 00:44:40.815
-[gasps]
-[Kara squeals. giggles]

714
00:44:40.948 --> 00:44:43.117
[Kara. in common tongue]
<i>Honestly. I didn't have a clue</i>

715
00:44:43.251 --> 00:44:47.255
<i>that Argo was different</i>
<i>from any other planet.</i>

716
00:44:47.387 --> 00:44:48.488
[laughter]

717
00:44:48.923 --> 00:44:50.591
[Kara] <i>I thought we were lucky.</i>

718
00:44:51.893 --> 00:44:54.294
<i>But luck.</i>
<i>almost by definition.</i>

719
00:44:54.427 --> 00:44:55.328
<i>runs out.</i>

720
00:44:55.462 --> 00:44:57.665
[coughing]

721
00:44:58.800 --> 00:45:01.334
[melancholy music playing]

722
00:45:02.435 --> 00:45:04.071
[panting]

723
00:45:05.405 --> 00:45:06.574
[speaking Kryptonian]
Tell me.

724
00:45:08.509 --> 00:45:11.112
When Argo City broke off.
it unearthed...

725
00:45:11.245 --> 00:45:15.750
a crystalline mineral
buried deep in the planet.

726
00:45:16.918 --> 00:45:17.652
Kryptonite.

727
00:45:18.886 --> 00:45:21.923
The soil has been poisoned.

728
00:45:22.223 --> 00:45:24.892
People are ill all over Argo...

729
00:45:25.059 --> 00:45:27.695
and it's spreading.

730
00:45:29.362 --> 00:45:32.399
And can it be helped?

731
00:45:37.370 --> 00:45:40.041
[panicked clamor in distance]

732
00:45:43.578 --> 00:45:45.378
[man groaning]

733
00:45:48.916 --> 00:45:49.684
[speaking Kryptonian]
Kara.

734
00:45:51.451 --> 00:45:52.753
What is all this?

735
00:45:54.487 --> 00:45:58.926
Trying to preserve Argo with
my force field was a failure.

736
00:45:59.694 --> 00:46:03.831
The radiation
has taken hold of me. too.

737
00:46:05.633 --> 00:46:07.535
I cannot let it get you.

738
00:46:11.239 --> 00:46:14.441
I found my brother's sketches
for the escape pod.

739
00:46:15.343 --> 00:46:16.878
I made it big enough for you.

740
00:46:18.512 --> 00:46:20.948
You will follow your cousin.
Kal-El.

741
00:46:22.449 --> 00:46:25.519
You will make a new home
on Earth.

742
00:46:28.222 --> 00:46:28.923
No!

743
00:46:29.056 --> 00:46:30.390
[breath trembling]

744
00:46:30.524 --> 00:46:31.959
This is my home.

745
00:46:32.526 --> 00:46:36.429
This is my only home.

746
00:46:38.733 --> 00:46:41.535
Let the radiation take me too.

747
00:46:42.136 --> 00:46:46.073
I'll lie in the ground
next to you and next to mom.

748
00:46:48.408 --> 00:46:49.377
[stammers]

749
00:46:49.677 --> 00:46:51.913
I am one tiny life.

750
00:46:52.780 --> 00:46:56.550
What difference does it make
whether I live or die?

751
00:46:56.684 --> 00:46:59.887
You are not one tiny life.

752
00:47:00.788 --> 00:47:03.858
You are your mother's life.

753
00:47:05.026 --> 00:47:07.028
You are my life.

754
00:47:07.895 --> 00:47:11.666
You are our souls
unfolding into the future.

755
00:47:12.733 --> 00:47:14.201
My child...

756
00:47:14.702 --> 00:47:17.705
this is why you must live.

757
00:47:19.573 --> 00:47:21.943
[labored breathing]

758
00:47:30.217 --> 00:47:31.919
When I am gone.

759
00:47:33.154 --> 00:47:37.024
I need you
to promise me something.

760
00:47:37.725 --> 00:47:39.026
Of course. mother.

761
00:47:40.761 --> 00:47:42.930
Just be good.

762
00:47:43.064 --> 00:47:47.268
That doesn't mean
you cannot be tough.

763
00:47:47.401 --> 00:47:50.838
And that doesn't mean
you have to be nice.

764
00:47:53.207 --> 00:47:55.076
But you must be good.

765
00:47:57.111 --> 00:47:59.513
[bell tolling]

766
00:48:04.085 --> 00:48:06.854
[Zor-El speaking Kryptonian]
We do not choose our paths.

767
00:48:08.723 --> 00:48:11.258
Your path
will be one of great effort...

768
00:48:13.527 --> 00:48:15.930
of great purpose.

769
00:48:17.798 --> 00:48:22.937
Where you are going.
you will have enormous power.

770
00:48:24.572 --> 00:48:25.806
[Zor-El]
Use it to protect those...

771
00:48:25.940 --> 00:48:28.142
who cannot protect themselves.

772
00:48:29.777 --> 00:48:31.645
Trust yourself...

773
00:48:31.979 --> 00:48:33.614
to know what is right. Kara.

774
00:48:40.688 --> 00:48:43.524
[melancholy music playing]

775
00:49:07.248 --> 00:49:09.050
[hatch beeping]

776
00:49:15.322 --> 00:49:16.724
We are with you.

777
00:49:17.591 --> 00:49:19.528
[machinery powering up]

778
00:49:19.660 --> 00:49:21.028
[sighs softly]

779
00:49:50.925 --> 00:49:52.159
[in common tongue] So. yeah.

780
00:49:54.929 --> 00:49:55.963
When I say
I know what it's like.

781
00:49:56.097 --> 00:49:58.265
I'm not talking
out of my ass. Ruthye.

782
00:49:58.399 --> 00:50:00.067
Grief is a killer. You know?

783
00:50:00.201 --> 00:50:02.103
It can make you want
to break bad. or...

784
00:50:03.170 --> 00:50:05.039
you know. get revenge. but...

785
00:50:08.275 --> 00:50:09.310
I don't think
any of those things

786
00:50:09.443 --> 00:50:11.612
are gonna lead you
to where you want to go.

787
00:50:15.382 --> 00:50:16.383
So. what does?

788
00:50:18.085 --> 00:50:20.054
When did you stop
feeling angry?

789
00:50:22.323 --> 00:50:23.891
Any day now.

790
00:50:30.831 --> 00:50:33.167
[melancholy music playing]

791
00:50:34.335 --> 00:50:35.970
[watch beeping]

792
00:50:40.141 --> 00:50:41.408
Um...

793
00:50:41.543 --> 00:50:43.043
I'm just gonna
go check on him.

794
00:50:43.811 --> 00:50:45.379
Stay here.

795
00:50:45.514 --> 00:50:47.314
[door slides]

796
00:50:53.320 --> 00:50:55.823
[indistinct discussion
in alien language]

797
00:51:09.403 --> 00:51:14.509
[both continue
speaking alien language]

798
00:51:15.109 --> 00:51:16.277
[in common tongue]
Where's your friend?

799
00:51:16.410 --> 00:51:18.679
They come now. Sit.

800
00:51:27.721 --> 00:51:28.856
[sighs]

801
00:51:32.426 --> 00:51:34.862
Recipe from my mother.

802
00:51:34.995 --> 00:51:37.064
from her mother.
mother. mother...

803
00:51:38.633 --> 00:51:41.368
-A little bitter.
-Thank you.

804
00:51:42.436 --> 00:51:43.404
Drink.

805
00:51:51.111 --> 00:51:53.648
[tense music playing]

806
00:51:54.516 --> 00:51:56.116
How does your friend
know the Brigands?

807
00:51:58.520 --> 00:52:01.088
We all know the Brigands.

808
00:52:03.357 --> 00:52:04.191
But you said--

809
00:52:04.325 --> 00:52:07.562
Brigands come here.
take girls.

810
00:52:07.696 --> 00:52:10.965
They come here.
take... our girl.

811
00:52:13.434 --> 00:52:14.468
Sarna.

812
00:52:15.936 --> 00:52:19.273
Yeah. your. um...
your daughter. the...

813
00:52:19.907 --> 00:52:21.375
The pictures.
[voice echoes distortedly]

814
00:52:23.744 --> 00:52:25.346
What did you give me?

815
00:52:26.113 --> 00:52:27.982
Sorry. Sorry. stop drinking.
Stop drinking.

816
00:52:28.115 --> 00:52:29.183
[speaking alien language]
Bomar. stop!

817
00:52:29.316 --> 00:52:31.318
It's for our daughter.
we have no choice.

818
00:52:31.452 --> 00:52:33.254
[in common tongue] Did you get
this poison from the Brigands?

819
00:52:33.387 --> 00:52:36.658
I-- No understand.
You should be...

820
00:52:36.790 --> 00:52:38.292
Paralyzed.

821
00:52:38.425 --> 00:52:40.294
[grunts] This is just
really gonna suck.

822
00:52:42.631 --> 00:52:44.098
Ow.

823
00:52:46.367 --> 00:52:47.801
Whoa.

824
00:52:48.603 --> 00:52:51.405
[grunting sharply]

825
00:52:51.939 --> 00:52:53.340
-[Kara] Milk.
-Why?

826
00:52:53.474 --> 00:52:56.477
Well. it coats your stomach
if you've been poisoned.

827
00:52:56.611 --> 00:52:57.712
Come on. man.

828
00:52:57.845 --> 00:52:59.146
It's a white liquid.

829
00:52:59.280 --> 00:53:00.914
-Door. Door.
-Help me out here.

830
00:53:09.189 --> 00:53:10.592
[chokes] What kind of milk
was that?

831
00:53:10.725 --> 00:53:11.925
Chewchan.

832
00:53:12.527 --> 00:53:13.628
[Kara] Chewchan.

833
00:53:13.762 --> 00:53:15.664
[groaning] Oh. my God. Okay.

834
00:53:16.196 --> 00:53:17.364
So. you sold me out...
for what?

835
00:53:17.498 --> 00:53:20.100
What are you... What are you
getting in return?

836
00:53:20.234 --> 00:53:21.402
Speak.

837
00:53:21.802 --> 00:53:24.104
One girl for two girls.

838
00:53:24.238 --> 00:53:26.574
[Kara gasping softly]

839
00:53:36.950 --> 00:53:38.553
[intruder snarling]

840
00:53:49.997 --> 00:53:51.865
[Kara retches]

841
00:53:56.870 --> 00:53:57.838
Hello.

842
00:53:57.971 --> 00:53:59.506
[Kara retching]

843
00:54:01.842 --> 00:54:03.010
Are you okay?

844
00:54:06.380 --> 00:54:08.415
I heard
you were looking for me.

845
00:54:08.550 --> 00:54:09.751
Huh?

846
00:54:09.883 --> 00:54:11.085
[Kara exclaims]

847
00:54:12.019 --> 00:54:13.521
You found me.

848
00:54:13.655 --> 00:54:15.456
Technically. you found me.

849
00:54:20.861 --> 00:54:22.062
[Krem bellows]

850
00:54:24.898 --> 00:54:26.166
[Krem grunts]

851
00:54:26.634 --> 00:54:27.935
Mm.

852
00:54:32.005 --> 00:54:33.874
[yelling]

853
00:54:38.412 --> 00:54:41.215
-[Brigands chuckling]
-[Kara panting]

854
00:54:42.650 --> 00:54:45.553
Hey. man. Can you just give me
one second?

855
00:54:46.755 --> 00:54:48.055
[both grunt]

856
00:54:49.923 --> 00:54:51.492
[Kara grunting]

857
00:54:51.626 --> 00:54:53.127
[retches]

858
00:54:56.230 --> 00:54:58.432
Thanks. I needed that.

859
00:54:58.566 --> 00:55:00.702
[Brigand roars]

860
00:55:01.235 --> 00:55:03.303
[intense music playing]

861
00:55:08.710 --> 00:55:10.277
[grunts]

862
00:55:10.911 --> 00:55:12.212
[Brigand groans]

863
00:55:14.314 --> 00:55:17.685
[Krem] You dropped
your puppy's antidote.

864
00:55:21.955 --> 00:55:23.056
[Ruthye shrieks] Kara!

865
00:55:25.527 --> 00:55:26.994
Help me!

866
00:55:29.062 --> 00:55:30.330
Help!

867
00:55:31.599 --> 00:55:33.400
[Ruthye screaming]

868
00:55:33.535 --> 00:55:35.135
No! [screaming]

869
00:55:36.470 --> 00:55:37.404
Kara!

870
00:55:42.109 --> 00:55:43.645
[Brigands grunt]

871
00:55:45.112 --> 00:55:46.648
[Brigand] Come on!

872
00:55:52.152 --> 00:55:53.855
[indistinct shouting]

873
00:55:53.987 --> 00:55:55.255
Whoa!

874
00:55:57.826 --> 00:55:59.126
Sorry!

875
00:56:01.930 --> 00:56:03.430
-Are you drunk?
-No!

876
00:56:05.365 --> 00:56:06.467
[Krem groans softly]

877
00:56:08.837 --> 00:56:10.304
Hey.

878
00:56:10.437 --> 00:56:12.540
She don't look very poisoned
to me. eh?

879
00:56:14.208 --> 00:56:15.309
[speaking alien language]
Bring me their daughter.

880
00:56:15.442 --> 00:56:16.644
Now.

881
00:56:17.077 --> 00:56:18.078
[in common tongue]
You smell of vomit.

882
00:56:18.212 --> 00:56:19.814
[Kara]
Because Mareck poisoned me.

883
00:56:20.481 --> 00:56:22.851
Oh. and I am fine.
thank you for asking.

884
00:56:22.983 --> 00:56:24.218
[tense music playing]

885
00:56:26.119 --> 00:56:27.321
[all scream]

886
00:56:34.995 --> 00:56:36.129
[people screaming]

887
00:56:43.470 --> 00:56:44.404
Huh.

888
00:56:47.909 --> 00:56:49.577
[indistinct clamor]

889
00:56:51.078 --> 00:56:52.614
[speaking alien language]
The brides!

890
00:56:52.747 --> 00:56:53.648
Get them! Get them!

891
00:56:57.451 --> 00:56:58.686
[in common tongue] Don't move.

892
00:57:01.623 --> 00:57:03.591
[people screaming. panicking]

893
00:57:05.492 --> 00:57:07.094
[grunts]

894
00:57:10.798 --> 00:57:12.232
[Brigand yells]

895
00:57:18.940 --> 00:57:20.307
[panting]

896
00:57:27.180 --> 00:57:28.215
[Brigands yelping]

897
00:57:28.348 --> 00:57:30.083
[Brigands groaning]

898
00:57:32.787 --> 00:57:33.755
Run.

899
00:57:47.067 --> 00:57:48.402
Drom Baxton.

900
00:57:49.003 --> 00:57:51.071
There's a lot of rich dipshits
looking for you.

901
00:57:51.204 --> 00:57:52.740
Screw you. old man.

902
00:57:53.073 --> 00:57:54.441
[laughs]

903
00:57:55.175 --> 00:57:56.544
Shit.

904
00:58:09.356 --> 00:58:11.626
-Sarna! Sarna!
-Sarna! Sarna! Sarna!

905
00:58:11.759 --> 00:58:13.327
[speaking alien language]
A deal is a deal.

906
00:58:14.194 --> 00:58:15.362
She has to die.

907
00:58:15.495 --> 00:58:17.130
-[in common tongue] No!
-Sarna!

908
00:58:20.001 --> 00:58:21.703
-[cackling]
-[engine revving]

909
00:58:21.836 --> 00:58:23.838
[screams]

910
00:58:24.371 --> 00:58:26.206
[Brigands groaning]

911
00:58:32.346 --> 00:58:34.882
[grunting]

912
00:58:36.183 --> 00:58:37.417
Ouch.

913
00:58:37.552 --> 00:58:39.587
["Safeword" by Halsey playing]

914
00:58:41.022 --> 00:58:42.456
[Brigand screams]

915
00:58:44.324 --> 00:58:45.459
[yells in pain]

916
00:58:45.593 --> 00:58:46.995
Aren't you the ditz
from that dive bar?

917
00:58:47.127 --> 00:58:48.062
Funny.

918
00:58:48.863 --> 00:58:50.031
That's what
I've been calling you.

919
00:58:50.163 --> 00:58:51.298
Touché!

920
00:58:53.467 --> 00:58:55.168
[all yelling. grunting]

921
00:59:11.284 --> 00:59:13.487
[Brigand yelling]

922
00:59:25.332 --> 00:59:27.602
[laughing]

923
00:59:34.174 --> 00:59:35.910
[Brigand screams]

924
00:59:36.044 --> 00:59:37.411
[thud]

925
00:59:37.545 --> 00:59:39.947
[fighting continues
in distance]

926
00:59:40.081 --> 00:59:42.482
[tense music playing]

927
00:59:43.785 --> 00:59:46.353
[panting]

928
00:59:47.287 --> 00:59:48.690
[humming]

929
00:59:49.824 --> 00:59:50.825
[chuckles]

930
00:59:55.163 --> 00:59:56.396
[engine revs]

931
00:59:56.531 --> 00:59:58.365
Oh. that's ballsy.

932
00:59:58.498 --> 01:00:01.135
Drom Baxton!
You just made me angry.

933
01:00:01.268 --> 01:00:02.737
[person screaming]

934
01:00:08.241 --> 01:00:10.477
[Brigand screams]

935
01:00:11.512 --> 01:00:12.647
Got you. bastich.

936
01:00:22.355 --> 01:00:24.257
[sing-song] Sarna.

937
01:00:26.094 --> 01:00:28.096
Where are you?

938
01:00:28.529 --> 01:00:30.932
You okay? Yeah?
Okay. get her out of here.

939
01:00:31.065 --> 01:00:33.500
She's the last one. Go. Go!

940
01:00:34.367 --> 01:00:36.804
[dramatic music playing]

941
01:00:48.348 --> 01:00:51.185
Come on. Krem.
Where's my antidote?

942
01:00:51.753 --> 01:00:53.721
[Krem] You like to play games.

943
01:00:54.889 --> 01:00:56.858
I can play games.

944
01:01:03.631 --> 01:01:06.868
I can smell you. [chuckles]

945
01:01:09.237 --> 01:01:10.938
[sniffing]

946
01:01:19.914 --> 01:01:21.516
[Ruthye yells]

947
01:01:25.620 --> 01:01:27.021
-I told you not to move.
-I had him.

948
01:01:27.155 --> 01:01:28.455
Hide.

949
01:01:34.228 --> 01:01:35.395
Shit!

950
01:01:37.865 --> 01:01:38.833
Sarna!

951
01:01:40.201 --> 01:01:41.501
[Sarna screams]

952
01:01:42.703 --> 01:01:43.971
Bye-bye.

953
01:01:44.371 --> 01:01:45.807
No! No!

954
01:01:45.940 --> 01:01:49.376
-[weapon sweeps]
-[Krem laughing]

955
01:01:49.510 --> 01:01:50.945
[bellows]

956
01:02:11.464 --> 01:02:13.801
[thunderclap]

957
01:02:18.840 --> 01:02:20.241
-[grunts]
-They're dead.

958
01:02:20.373 --> 01:02:22.610
Because you did not let me do
what had to be done!

959
01:02:22.743 --> 01:02:24.745
Okay. Ruthye. I'm not
letting you kill that man.

960
01:02:24.879 --> 01:02:27.480
Why not? Look at the suffering
he leaves in his wake.

961
01:02:27.615 --> 01:02:29.250
Why does he get to be alive?
Why?

962
01:02:29.382 --> 01:02:30.952
Okay! Okay. stop freaking out!

963
01:02:31.085 --> 01:02:34.522
Get off! Don't tell me
not to freak out.

964
01:02:34.655 --> 01:02:36.324
I'm allowed.

965
01:02:36.456 --> 01:02:37.592
Tell me why.

966
01:02:37.725 --> 01:02:39.392
Because it'll mess you up.

967
01:02:39.794 --> 01:02:42.395
You think it will make you
feel better? It won't.

968
01:02:42.763 --> 01:02:44.665
It'll haunt you
for the rest of your life.

969
01:02:44.799 --> 01:02:46.100
Is that what you want?

970
01:02:48.002 --> 01:02:49.837
So. the alternative
is to be like you?

971
01:02:50.738 --> 01:02:52.372
Constantly leaving your planet

972
01:02:52.505 --> 01:02:53.641
to drink yourself
into a stupor?

973
01:02:54.642 --> 01:02:55.843
Drunk all of the time

974
01:02:55.977 --> 01:02:57.612
so you never
have to feel anything?

975
01:02:57.745 --> 01:03:00.548
Guess what? I too want
to free myself of this pain.

976
01:03:00.915 --> 01:03:02.583
And I do not want
to be like you.

977
01:03:03.517 --> 01:03:04.685
Okay.

978
01:03:05.820 --> 01:03:07.121
Then why don't you go find

979
01:03:07.255 --> 01:03:09.257
whatever dimensional portal
he just passed through

980
01:03:09.389 --> 01:03:10.925
all by yourself?

981
01:03:18.566 --> 01:03:20.735
[indistinct shouting]

982
01:03:27.440 --> 01:03:29.143
[breathes deeply]

983
01:03:33.480 --> 01:03:35.650
[somber music playing]

984
01:04:02.310 --> 01:04:03.811
[inaudible]

985
01:04:07.615 --> 01:04:09.951
[inaudible]

986
01:04:20.528 --> 01:04:22.663
[suspenseful music playing]

987
01:04:29.637 --> 01:04:31.272
[speaking alien language]

988
01:04:31.973 --> 01:04:33.374
[in common tongue]
Hey! Squidward!

989
01:04:33.506 --> 01:04:34.442
Where are the Brigands?

990
01:04:34.575 --> 01:04:36.243
-No idea.
-Really?

991
01:04:36.377 --> 01:04:38.145
-Aargh!
-Bullshit.

992
01:04:38.279 --> 01:04:40.948
I have less than 24 hours
to save my dog.

993
01:04:41.082 --> 01:04:42.850
so you tell me
where the Brigands are

994
01:04:42.984 --> 01:04:45.586
and I won't turn you
into a hand puppet. Okay?

995
01:04:45.720 --> 01:04:47.021
[gasping] Okay.

996
01:04:48.488 --> 01:04:49.890
[groans]

997
01:04:51.759 --> 01:04:55.663
Okay.
But you'll have to wear this.

998
01:05:01.369 --> 01:05:02.403
Let's go.

999
01:05:02.536 --> 01:05:04.638
[suspenseful music playing]

1000
01:05:12.813 --> 01:05:14.682
[alien snoring]

1001
01:05:33.834 --> 01:05:35.703
[landing gear clunks]

1002
01:05:37.805 --> 01:05:39.607
[criminal]
This is as close as we get.

1003
01:05:54.555 --> 01:05:56.891
[breathing heavily]

1004
01:06:00.428 --> 01:06:02.296
[wheezing]

1005
01:06:02.430 --> 01:06:04.932
[discordant music playing]

1006
01:06:14.708 --> 01:06:17.044
[continues wheezing]

1007
01:06:31.492 --> 01:06:33.594
[engine roar fades]

1008
01:06:49.243 --> 01:06:50.244
Hi. there.

1009
01:06:50.377 --> 01:06:51.378
[Krypto barks]

1010
01:06:53.013 --> 01:06:54.648
I've been tracking your ship
for the last month.

1011
01:06:54.782 --> 01:06:57.084
I believe you're from Krypton?

1012
01:06:57.218 --> 01:06:58.219
And so am I.

1013
01:06:58.352 --> 01:06:59.987
[Krypto growling]

1014
01:07:00.121 --> 01:07:01.455
Clark.

1015
01:07:02.289 --> 01:07:03.691
[speaking Kryptonian]
I don't understand you.

1016
01:07:04.325 --> 01:07:05.626
Where am I?

1017
01:07:05.860 --> 01:07:07.962
Is this Earth?

1018
01:07:08.896 --> 01:07:10.131
-Are you Kal-El?
-[barks]

1019
01:07:10.264 --> 01:07:12.333
[sighs. in English]
I'm sorry. I don't...

1020
01:07:12.466 --> 01:07:13.367
I don't. um...

1021
01:07:14.435 --> 01:07:15.503
I don't speak Kryptonian.

1022
01:07:15.636 --> 01:07:16.804
I didn't ever...

1023
01:07:17.371 --> 01:07:19.874
Shoot. I...
I wasn't raised there. so...

1024
01:07:20.007 --> 01:07:20.941
[louder]
I wasn't raised there!

1025
01:07:21.075 --> 01:07:22.209
Why am I talking louder?

1026
01:07:22.343 --> 01:07:23.545
Let me help you.

1027
01:07:23.677 --> 01:07:25.279
[Kara speaking Kryptonian]
Krypto. be good. buddy.

1028
01:07:26.180 --> 01:07:27.047
Be good.

1029
01:07:27.181 --> 01:07:28.082
[in English]
He's a feisty little guy.

1030
01:07:28.215 --> 01:07:30.084
-[Krypto growling]
-He's cute.

1031
01:07:31.018 --> 01:07:32.253
Is it okay if I...

1032
01:07:37.526 --> 01:07:38.692
Watch your step there.

1033
01:07:39.460 --> 01:07:40.961
Might be slippery. so...

1034
01:07:41.095 --> 01:07:43.197
Is this... I'll grab it.

1035
01:07:44.698 --> 01:07:45.866
Okay.

1036
01:07:46.834 --> 01:07:48.936
Ah. yeah. Pretty cool. huh?

1037
01:07:50.971 --> 01:07:52.907
Don't worry.
we don't actually live here.

1038
01:07:53.340 --> 01:07:55.376
There's a lot more to Earth
than just this place.

1039
01:07:56.611 --> 01:07:58.613
Big city. Lots of stuff to do.

1040
01:07:58.746 --> 01:08:00.615
-[Krypto barking]
-Bowling. that's fun.

1041
01:08:00.748 --> 01:08:02.116
It was a big adjustment
for me.

1042
01:08:02.249 --> 01:08:03.250
You know. coming from Kansas.

1043
01:08:03.384 --> 01:08:05.554
You know.
small town kinda guy. but...

1044
01:08:05.686 --> 01:08:06.921
You know Kansas?

1045
01:08:07.054 --> 01:08:08.722
No. Why would you know Kansas?

1046
01:08:08.856 --> 01:08:11.258
What am I...? [sighs]

1047
01:08:11.392 --> 01:08:13.460
You can't understand a word
that I'm saying right now.

1048
01:08:15.597 --> 01:08:17.932
It's okay. You will one day.

1049
01:08:18.332 --> 01:08:21.268
And you'll also learn to love
this place just like I have.

1050
01:08:22.303 --> 01:08:23.304
Promise.

1051
01:08:27.007 --> 01:08:28.842
[speaks Kryptonian]
Why is he in his underwear?

1052
01:08:28.976 --> 01:08:30.444
[in English] Oh.
Should mention.

1053
01:08:32.379 --> 01:08:35.650
Your powers are gonna start
kicking in right about...

1054
01:08:35.783 --> 01:08:36.850
now.

1055
01:08:36.984 --> 01:08:39.119
[horns blaring loudly]

1056
01:08:39.253 --> 01:08:41.455
-[indistinct amplified voices]
-[sirens blaring]

1057
01:08:51.298 --> 01:08:53.067
[speaks Kryptonian]
How can this be home?

1058
01:08:53.200 --> 01:08:55.369
[loud noises outside continue]

1059
01:09:00.609 --> 01:09:02.443
[noises become muffled]

1060
01:09:05.179 --> 01:09:08.115
["Care" by Hana Vu playing
over headphones]

1061
01:09:08.749 --> 01:09:10.184
[sighs softly]

1062
01:09:17.791 --> 01:09:19.793
[exhales slowly]

1063
01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:27.602
[barks]

1064
01:09:27.736 --> 01:09:29.270
[growls playfully]

1065
01:09:46.655 --> 01:09:48.989
[chuckling]

1066
01:09:50.324 --> 01:09:52.926
-[music stops abruptly]
-[gasping]

1067
01:09:58.533 --> 01:10:00.367
I thought that the shelter
might help.

1068
01:10:00.769 --> 01:10:01.770
Was I right?

1069
01:10:01.902 --> 01:10:03.003
[weakly] Wait...

1070
01:10:03.837 --> 01:10:04.938
What did you...

1071
01:10:05.072 --> 01:10:06.173
I saw you boarding
that man's ship.

1072
01:10:06.307 --> 01:10:08.008
so I snuck up
into the cargo hold.

1073
01:10:08.909 --> 01:10:09.977
What's this place?

1074
01:10:10.110 --> 01:10:11.879
[chuckles weakly]

1075
01:10:14.081 --> 01:10:15.983
It's my prison.

1076
01:10:16.116 --> 01:10:19.486
The Brigands know that
the planet orbits between...

1077
01:10:20.454 --> 01:10:21.523
two suns.

1078
01:10:23.090 --> 01:10:24.825
And that the green sun...

1079
01:10:26.093 --> 01:10:27.261
can kill me.

1080
01:10:31.065 --> 01:10:33.834
Krem left your ship on Bilquis
and I found this.

1081
01:10:35.670 --> 01:10:36.837
Thought that it might help.

1082
01:10:36.970 --> 01:10:38.906
[melancholy music playing]

1083
01:10:40.374 --> 01:10:43.444
It's... It's just
a stupid suit. Ruthye.

1084
01:10:45.979 --> 01:10:48.182
It doesn't do anything.

1085
01:10:50.451 --> 01:10:52.620
[wheezes]

1086
01:10:58.959 --> 01:11:00.595
My dog...

1087
01:11:00.729 --> 01:11:02.930
[breathing heavily]

1088
01:11:06.433 --> 01:11:07.935
My Krypto.

1089
01:11:09.336 --> 01:11:10.904
I'm not there to say goodbye.

1090
01:11:11.038 --> 01:11:12.807
-Hey.
-[Kara] He...

1091
01:11:12.940 --> 01:11:16.310
-I just want...
-Hey. Kara.

1092
01:11:17.878 --> 01:11:19.012
Don't freak out.

1093
01:11:30.592 --> 01:11:33.227
I'm so sorry for saying
I didn't want to be like you.

1094
01:11:33.994 --> 01:11:35.329
[Ruthye sniffling]

1095
01:11:37.532 --> 01:11:38.600
I mean...

1096
01:11:40.668 --> 01:11:42.637
you're not always nice.
but you're kind.

1097
01:11:44.672 --> 01:11:47.141
And you're not always perfect.
but you're good.

1098
01:11:52.179 --> 01:11:54.047
So. thank you
for taking me with you.

1099
01:12:07.695 --> 01:12:09.029
Water.

1100
01:12:10.431 --> 01:12:12.099
[coughing]

1101
01:12:15.804 --> 01:12:17.938
[unsettled music playing]

1102
01:12:43.832 --> 01:12:46.033
[men shouting in distance
in alien language]

1103
01:13:00.981 --> 01:13:02.115
[thud]

1104
01:13:03.050 --> 01:13:05.285
[engines rumbling]

1105
01:13:10.725 --> 01:13:12.760
[creature squeaking]

1106
01:13:16.163 --> 01:13:18.031
[Ruthye moans softly]

1107
01:13:20.133 --> 01:13:21.703
[gasps]

1108
01:13:26.473 --> 01:13:27.642
[grunts]

1109
01:13:33.413 --> 01:13:34.749
[prisoner snoring]

1110
01:13:37.886 --> 01:13:39.754
[breathing heavily]

1111
01:13:42.122 --> 01:13:44.124
[grunting]

1112
01:13:53.668 --> 01:13:55.003
-[creature squealing]
-Gotcha.

1113
01:13:55.135 --> 01:13:56.538
-[snap]
-[squealing stops abruptly]

1114
01:13:56.671 --> 01:13:58.105
[suit powers down]

1115
01:13:59.941 --> 01:14:01.108
Thank you...

1116
01:14:02.175 --> 01:14:03.343
I guess.

1117
01:14:03.477 --> 01:14:05.078
[Lobo] Top of those bars
are poison-tipped.

1118
01:14:05.212 --> 01:14:07.080
It's a painful
and noisy death.

1119
01:14:07.214 --> 01:14:08.716
So if you could wait
until after my nap.

1120
01:14:08.850 --> 01:14:09.851
that would be great.

1121
01:14:09.984 --> 01:14:12.219
-And why should I trust you?
-You shouldn't.

1122
01:14:12.654 --> 01:14:14.454
But I'd trust me
more than a Brigand.

1123
01:14:14.589 --> 01:14:16.290
My assumption is
that you've tried and failed

1124
01:14:16.423 --> 01:14:18.258
at numerous ways
to get out of here.

1125
01:14:21.930 --> 01:14:23.463
Why are you in here?

1126
01:14:24.131 --> 01:14:25.633
You're not gonna let me nap.
are you?

1127
01:14:25.767 --> 01:14:28.036
-Did you get caught?
-Hunters don't get caught.

1128
01:14:28.168 --> 01:14:30.939
They set traps
and then they wait.

1129
01:14:31.071 --> 01:14:32.372
Well. I'm not interested
in waiting.

1130
01:14:32.506 --> 01:14:34.642
Soon. I will find Krem
and do what needs to be done.

1131
01:14:36.744 --> 01:14:38.813
Is there a bounty on his head
that I don't know about?

1132
01:14:38.947 --> 01:14:41.749
No! I'm not after the money.
I'm after the revenge.

1133
01:14:42.449 --> 01:14:44.318
Ugh. Overrated.

1134
01:14:44.451 --> 01:14:45.820
He murdered my innocent
and honorable family

1135
01:14:45.954 --> 01:14:46.988
in cold blood.

1136
01:14:47.120 --> 01:14:48.155
Well. there must have been
a reason.

1137
01:14:48.288 --> 01:14:49.857
We gave him what he came for.

1138
01:14:50.357 --> 01:14:52.560
He killed them for nothing.
For sport.

1139
01:14:52.694 --> 01:14:53.695
That's a reason.

1140
01:14:53.828 --> 01:14:56.196
He has no honor. No...

1141
01:14:56.898 --> 01:14:57.832
code.

1142
01:14:59.366 --> 01:15:00.702
Like you. I can imagine.

1143
01:15:01.268 --> 01:15:04.906
My code is iron.
you little shit.

1144
01:15:05.039 --> 01:15:09.476
And make no mistake.
I kill for money. not sport.

1145
01:15:10.177 --> 01:15:11.813
And I never go back
on my word.

1146
01:15:11.946 --> 01:15:13.447
[door opening]

1147
01:15:17.552 --> 01:15:20.153
[speaking alien language]
A dead Kryptonian...

1148
01:15:20.354 --> 01:15:23.891
should make
for a magnificent trophy.

1149
01:15:24.025 --> 01:15:26.393
I'm working on it.

1150
01:15:27.795 --> 01:15:29.831
-[tense music playing]
-[keys rattling]

1151
01:15:41.743 --> 01:15:42.910
[grunts]

1152
01:15:45.680 --> 01:15:48.181
[in common tongue] I think
your friend is in trouble.

1153
01:15:49.483 --> 01:15:51.318
If she's still alive.

1154
01:15:52.620 --> 01:15:53.588
Yes.

1155
01:15:54.922 --> 01:15:56.758
You know. green sun...

1156
01:15:56.891 --> 01:15:58.926
and Kryptonian...

1157
01:15:59.661 --> 01:16:02.063
is not good combination.
you know?

1158
01:16:02.462 --> 01:16:03.765
Is very difficult.

1159
01:16:04.666 --> 01:16:05.900
You fragile excuse for a man.

1160
01:16:06.034 --> 01:16:07.135
What?

1161
01:16:07.669 --> 01:16:09.269
More revolting
than the excrement

1162
01:16:09.403 --> 01:16:10.638
on the bottom of your shoe.

1163
01:16:10.772 --> 01:16:11.906
Wow.

1164
01:16:12.040 --> 01:16:15.543
So many words! Cool!

1165
01:16:17.078 --> 01:16:18.813
But you don't need them here.

1166
01:16:19.179 --> 01:16:21.415
I'm going to tell you something.
Hm?

1167
01:16:23.951 --> 01:16:25.753
Come on. turn around.

1168
01:16:25.887 --> 01:16:26.788
Look at me.

1169
01:16:29.057 --> 01:16:31.191
I want to propose a deal.

1170
01:16:31.559 --> 01:16:34.862
You tell me
where we can find your friend

1171
01:16:34.996 --> 01:16:36.496
and I will let you live.

1172
01:16:38.933 --> 01:16:39.901
Huh?

1173
01:16:43.203 --> 01:16:44.471
[spits]

1174
01:16:49.911 --> 01:16:51.311
Bye-bye.

1175
01:16:56.450 --> 01:16:59.319
This one dies
before the end of the day.

1176
01:17:08.830 --> 01:17:09.964
[door slams]

1177
01:17:11.264 --> 01:17:12.934
[locks clicking]

1178
01:17:14.001 --> 01:17:15.937
[unsettled music playing]

1179
01:17:18.639 --> 01:17:21.008
[labored breathing]

1180
01:17:35.123 --> 01:17:38.126
[Ruthye] <i>Please.</i>
<i>I don't want to die.</i>

1181
01:17:38.926 --> 01:17:41.929
Please. just don't--
Don't let me die.

1182
01:17:42.063 --> 01:17:43.765
Come on. I'm begging you.

1183
01:17:43.898 --> 01:17:46.033
Please just...
just take me to Krem.

1184
01:17:46.567 --> 01:17:48.169
Please. just take me to Krem!

1185
01:17:48.301 --> 01:17:51.038
I'll tell him where
he can find my friend. Please.

1186
01:17:51.172 --> 01:17:52.540
[speaking alien language]
Get off your fat ass...

1187
01:17:53.007 --> 01:17:53.975
and take her to Krem.

1188
01:17:54.108 --> 01:17:55.308
He'll shut her up.

1189
01:18:02.583 --> 01:18:03.718
[in common tongue] Thank you.

1190
01:18:03.851 --> 01:18:05.285
Won't you just take me
to Krem?

1191
01:18:05.418 --> 01:18:06.621
I'll be good. I promise.

1192
01:18:09.857 --> 01:18:11.559
I promise. I'll do...
I'll do whatever he says.

1193
01:18:11.692 --> 01:18:13.594
I'll tell him
what he needs to know.

1194
01:18:14.929 --> 01:18:15.596
[speaks alien language]
Keep your trap shut

1195
01:18:15.730 --> 01:18:16.798
and do as you're told.

1196
01:18:16.931 --> 01:18:18.298
[in common tongue]
Thank you so much.

1197
01:18:19.100 --> 01:18:20.500
[yells]

1198
01:18:21.434 --> 01:18:22.637
[guard grunting]

1199
01:18:22.770 --> 01:18:24.071
[intense music playing]

1200
01:18:26.073 --> 01:18:27.307
[Brigand groans]

1201
01:18:27.440 --> 01:18:28.743
Yes!

1202
01:18:45.693 --> 01:18:47.895
[Lobo laughing. applauding]

1203
01:18:49.163 --> 01:18:50.064
That was amazing.

1204
01:18:51.899 --> 01:18:54.635
You're a little savage.
aren't ya? I knew it.

1205
01:18:55.435 --> 01:18:57.437
[grunting]

1206
01:18:57.572 --> 01:18:59.807
[Lobo] I knew
you had it in you.

1207
01:18:59.941 --> 01:19:01.108
I could see it.

1208
01:19:01.242 --> 01:19:02.844
[sing-song] Come back.

1209
01:19:03.343 --> 01:19:05.012
Aren't you
forgetting something?

1210
01:19:05.980 --> 01:19:07.281
Come on back.

1211
01:19:07.782 --> 01:19:09.150
-[Ruthye] Fine.
-There she is.

1212
01:19:09.283 --> 01:19:10.818
[Ruthye] But only if you help
us take down the Brigands.

1213
01:19:10.952 --> 01:19:13.654
Oh. they're gonna suffer.
[laughs]

1214
01:19:15.122 --> 01:19:16.858
-Yeah!
-[grunts]

1215
01:19:17.792 --> 01:19:19.160
I'm very proud of you.

1216
01:19:19.293 --> 01:19:20.895
Told you my plan would work.

1217
01:19:22.395 --> 01:19:24.732
Deck's this way. I get
my chopper and my gut hook.

1218
01:19:24.866 --> 01:19:27.001
-I'm gonna slash--
-[metal creaking]

1219
01:19:29.237 --> 01:19:30.805
That is very impressive.

1220
01:19:31.539 --> 01:19:33.007
Little shit.

1221
01:19:33.140 --> 01:19:35.142
[Ruthye panting]

1222
01:19:39.313 --> 01:19:41.414
[tense music playing]

1223
01:19:53.160 --> 01:19:54.662
[footsteps approaching]

1224
01:19:56.429 --> 01:19:58.065
[indistinct conversation]

1225
01:20:06.274 --> 01:20:07.440
[clothing unfastens]

1226
01:20:07.575 --> 01:20:08.809
[liquid splashing]

1227
01:20:37.838 --> 01:20:39.640
[labored breathing]

1228
01:20:41.175 --> 01:20:43.577
[stirring music playing]

1229
01:21:04.632 --> 01:21:05.800
[speaking Kryptonian]
Where you are going.

1230
01:21:05.933 --> 01:21:07.535
you will have enormous power.

1231
01:21:07.702 --> 01:21:09.603
I need you to promise me
something.

1232
01:21:09.737 --> 01:21:12.206
[in English] I know
it's pretty colorful. but...

1233
01:21:12.440 --> 01:21:13.908
[Zor-El speaking Kryptonian]
Use it to protect those...

1234
01:21:14.041 --> 01:21:16.043
who cannot protect themselves.

1235
01:21:16.177 --> 01:21:18.446
[in English] ...that's just so
everyone knows we're...

1236
01:21:18.579 --> 01:21:19.647
<i>good.</i>

1237
01:21:19.780 --> 01:21:21.716
[breathes heavily]

1238
01:21:26.420 --> 01:21:28.923
[wondrous music playing]

1239
01:21:39.934 --> 01:21:42.036
[suspenseful music playing]

1240
01:21:42.169 --> 01:21:43.838
[indistinct clamor]

1241
01:21:53.180 --> 01:21:55.016
[shouting enthusiastically
in alien language]

1242
01:22:05.259 --> 01:22:07.828
-[foreboding music playing]
-[chuckling]

1243
01:22:11.399 --> 01:22:13.901
[grunting]

1244
01:22:16.971 --> 01:22:18.372
[in common tongue] I heard
you were calling me

1245
01:22:18.506 --> 01:22:20.274
from down there.
is that true?

1246
01:22:22.676 --> 01:22:25.046
Yeah. [laughs] Ooh.

1247
01:22:28.816 --> 01:22:31.085
[murmurs thoughtfully]

1248
01:22:33.254 --> 01:22:35.289
Ah. Mmm.

1249
01:22:38.692 --> 01:22:40.094
Look at me.

1250
01:22:40.828 --> 01:22:42.096
Look at me.

1251
01:22:43.564 --> 01:22:44.533
Hm?

1252
01:22:44.665 --> 01:22:45.766
[Krem chuckles]

1253
01:22:46.500 --> 01:22:47.768
Do it.

1254
01:22:48.335 --> 01:22:49.603
Better make it quick.

1255
01:22:55.643 --> 01:22:57.812
[triumphant music playing]

1256
01:23:13.761 --> 01:23:15.896
-[Ruthye yelps]
-[grunts]

1257
01:23:18.132 --> 01:23:19.300
[grunts]

1258
01:23:20.234 --> 01:23:23.037
You know. we haven't been
formally introduced.

1259
01:23:24.839 --> 01:23:26.941
Hi. I'm the bitch
whose dog you shot.

1260
01:23:28.409 --> 01:23:30.111
[intense music playing]

1261
01:23:31.212 --> 01:23:33.180
Whew! [chuckles]

1262
01:23:33.681 --> 01:23:34.915
[growls]

1263
01:23:35.683 --> 01:23:37.051
[Brigand yells]

1264
01:23:39.687 --> 01:23:40.888
[yells]

1265
01:23:42.490 --> 01:23:43.991
[screaming]

1266
01:23:55.803 --> 01:23:57.738
[brigands yelling]

1267
01:24:15.656 --> 01:24:17.124
[gasping]

1268
01:24:18.192 --> 01:24:19.126
[grunts]

1269
01:24:19.660 --> 01:24:20.629
[grunts]

1270
01:24:20.761 --> 01:24:22.796
[Krem chuckling]

1271
01:24:24.566 --> 01:24:25.966
[continues chuckling]

1272
01:24:27.569 --> 01:24:29.670
Feel the power!

1273
01:24:29.803 --> 01:24:31.705
-Huh? Look at this.
-[Kara gasping]

1274
01:24:31.839 --> 01:24:34.141
I made it especially
for you. as present.

1275
01:24:34.576 --> 01:24:36.343
It's Kryptonite Delight.

1276
01:24:37.411 --> 01:24:39.113
It's Kryptonite crystal.

1277
01:24:39.780 --> 01:24:43.384
I never tested it on anybody.
but looking at you...

1278
01:24:45.419 --> 01:24:47.454
it works. [chuckles]

1279
01:24:50.257 --> 01:24:52.426
Your eyes are beautiful
when you cry.

1280
01:24:52.561 --> 01:24:54.395
A lot of pain. huh?

1281
01:24:54.529 --> 01:24:56.297
Lot of suffering.

1282
01:24:56.997 --> 01:24:58.832
I don't like
to see you suffer.

1283
01:25:01.001 --> 01:25:03.103
So we will end the suffering.

1284
01:25:03.237 --> 01:25:04.205
Drom!

1285
01:25:20.754 --> 01:25:21.855
[weapon sweeps]

1286
01:25:24.693 --> 01:25:25.893
[cackling]

1287
01:25:26.595 --> 01:25:27.895
Got you. bastich!

1288
01:25:28.028 --> 01:25:29.531
Travel-size is always easier.

1289
01:25:29.664 --> 01:25:31.065
["Don't Speak" by
Eagles of Death Metal playing]

1290
01:25:31.198 --> 01:25:33.801
-[yells]
-Not the abs.

1291
01:25:35.769 --> 01:25:37.071
[growls enthusiastically]

1292
01:25:37.204 --> 01:25:38.872
[grunts]

1293
01:25:41.742 --> 01:25:43.344
That was great kill.

1294
01:25:43.712 --> 01:25:46.180
[Krem laughs]

1295
01:25:48.282 --> 01:25:49.383
No!

1296
01:25:50.751 --> 01:25:52.253
The kid wants revenge.

1297
01:25:52.386 --> 01:25:54.054
-She should have it.
-It's not that simple.

1298
01:25:54.188 --> 01:25:56.123
Seems pretty simple to me.

1299
01:25:56.490 --> 01:25:57.626
[screams]

1300
